title: potato candy
directions: Add confectioners sugar to mashed potato until stiff and add vanilla.
Roll on waxed paper and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and slice thin.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve syrup.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water.
Add syrup and lemon juice.
Chill.
When partially set, add pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 5-cup ring mold.
Chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Make pudding by instructions on box.
Pour over fruit and leave overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute rice with garlic & onion in hot oil until starting to brown. Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is soft. Remove cover and finish cooking until mixture dries out somewhat.

title: lentil soup(serves 4)
directions: Put 2 tablespoons of the butter and all the oil in a soup pot; add the chopped onion and Prosciutto and turn on the heat to medium-high.
Do not cover the pot; cook the onion, stirring it, until it becomes a deep gold.
Add the chopped carrot and celery. Cook at lively heat for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the tomatoes with their juice and adjust the heat so that they bubble gently, but steadily.
Cook for about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Beat 2 eggs until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating until thickened.
Fold in baking powder, salt and flour. Blend in cooled chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts and flavoring. Measure 1 cup chocolate batter and set aside.
Spread remaining chocolate batter in a 9-inch square pan.
Pour cheese mixture on top.
Drop reserved chocolate batter by spoonfuls on cheese mixture; swirl the mixture together just to marble.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: bob's turkey casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
In large bowl, place soups, mushroom pieces and chopped onions.
(Onion may be steamed in small amount of water in microwave until soft.)
Mix together. Add peas and carrots as well as the turkey pieces.
Drain noodles and mix everything together.
Place in casserole sprayed with Pam. Crush crackers and place on top, drizzling butter on crackers. Bake until bubbly and heated throughout on 325°.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar; cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Gradually blend in confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and mix. Thin with milk, if needed.

title: clam spread
directions: Simmer clams and lemon juice for 15 to 20 minutes.
Saute remaining ingredients, except the breadcrumbs.
Add clams and juice to sauteed mixture along with unflavored breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve on crackers or party bread.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix well liquid ingredients and stir into dry ingredients. Mix only until dry ingredients are wet.
Cook on hot griddle that is slightly greased.
Reduce to low heat and cook until rim of each cake is free of bubbles and brown on bottom.
Brown on both sides.
Turn only once.

title: crispy cracker jack
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda; stir well, then pour over corn and mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out on table until cool.

title: 3 layer spicy carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Add eggs and oil, mix well. Add carrots and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Grease and flour 3 (9-inch pans). Preheat oven for 10 minutes at 350 degrees. Pour batter into pans and bake at 350 for 25 too 30 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes then turn out to cool. When cool spread layers and top with *filling.

title: protein grahams
directions: Place crackers side by side on jelly roll pan.
Boil butter and sugar 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; quickly pour and spread over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven; let settle a few seconds.
Remove to another cookie sheet.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add red food coloring and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, cocoa and baking soda.
Add the flour mixture to the sugar and egg mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in the vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes three 8-inch layers.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: Place butter in 1 quart measuring cup.
Microwave on High 1/2 minute.
Blend flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk. Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Layer half of potatoes, onion and sauce in greased 2 quart casserole; repeat layers and cover.
Microwave at High 17 to 19 minutes.
Stir after 10.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Add jello, butter and lemon juice.
Let stand in refrigerator until cool and thick.
Add berries and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream, a delicious summer dessert.

title: stuffed butternut or acorn squash
directions: Place squash face down in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Fill pan to 1/2-inch with boiling water. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter in same pan over low heat.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add rice.
Stir mixture together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix pudding, flour and sugar together.
Add the rest of the ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Makes 48 muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, Tang and pineapple juice.
Put all drained fruit in bowl and toss with dressing.
Put in large bowl and chill.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel, coarsely chop and set aside. Meanwhile, place cream, garlic, thyme and 4 tbsp. butter in a small pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Add mixture to potatoes.
Mash.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Place mixture in a large oven proof dish.
Dot with remaining butter, cover and bake 20 to 30 minutes, until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, shaved carrots, green pepper, onion may be used.

title: cheese strata
directions: Using donut cutter, cut 8 donuts from bread.
Set aside donuts and holes.
Fit scraps of bread into Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Place broken cheese slices over bread, then broccoli, then ham. Arrange donuts and holes on top in decorative manner.
Pour egg mixture over top, making sure top is wet.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, uncovered.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken in lemon-tomato sauce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside, reserving 1 crumbled strip. Reserve bacon fat.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon oil and butter until slightly browned. Drain off.
Add crumbled bacon and 1 tablespoon bacon fat. Add minced garlic and mix well. Grate 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese (slice and reserve remaining cheese).
Lightly salt cutlets and fill with the onion and cheese mixture.
Roll and seal with toothpicks.
Mix together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in eggs and bread crumbs.
Heat frying pan.
Add 3 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons bacon fat. Brown chicken on all sides. Cover pan and cook over medium heat.

In a saucepan, simmer tomato sauce, lemon juice, salt, pepper, sugar and 1 tablespoon bacon fat; also 1 strip crumbled bacon. When chicken is cooked, transfer to a baking dish. Top with slices of Mozzarella. Set under broiler to melt cheese.
Serve with sauce and white rice.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup of milk, meat and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking
mix and remainder of milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn custard casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet pea casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour in 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers mixed with butter (melted butter) over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add alternately the dry ingredients with milk.
Add vanilla.
Roll out on lightly floured counter; cut with biscuit cutter.
Pick up with slim spatula and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° (check oven).
Don't overbake.
Remove cakes while still warm. Re-grease cookie sheet and continue to bake more Tea Cakes.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients slowly to bubbling point, stirring frequently.
Add finely diced onion and sliced potatoes.
Heat slowly to boiling point.
Add chopped cheese, if desired.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Add potatoes and cream sauce.
Can add diced ham or diced wieners, if desired.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and brown sugar. Stir until well blended.
In a separate bowl, mix the eggs, milk, margarine and applesauce.
Make a well in the dry ingredients and stir in the applesauce mixture with quick strokes just until well moistened.
Fold in the nuts.
Spoon the batter into the muffin cups filling them 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pan-barbecued steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper; pound thoroughly.
Heat oil in a heavy saucepan or skillet (I use an iron pot) and brown steak on both sides, along with celery, onion and bell pepper. Drain fat, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
(I usually double sauce amounts and serve over mashed potatoes or rice.)

title: waldorf squares
directions: Combine flour and margarine and press in pan; bake 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients and blend well; spread over baked crust.
Return to oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool.
Frost and sprinkle with coconut.

title: mexican chicken stew
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients except onion to skillet; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce.
Heat to medium and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken and onion; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Transfer to baking dish. Combine 1/3 cup margarine, brown sugar, flour and nuts and sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Remove cream cheese from refrigerator; leave until softened. Sift sugar.
Melt chocolate.
Combine cheese and milk, beating until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, then add chocolate and blend. Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Press into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.
Makes 1 pound.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in tube cake pan at 300° until golden brown.

title: party salad
directions: Bring to a boil with 1 cup vinegar, sugar and salad oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
This salad can be prepared 24 hours ahead of time.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: new england sponge cake
directions: Separate the eggs and beat yolks until thick.
Add sugar gradually and beat thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and water.
Add salt to flour and combine mixtures.
Mix smooth and add beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased tubular pan.
Bake 1 hour in oven at 300°; increase heat to 325° after first fifteen minutes.
Take from oven; invert pan and let cool.
Remove from pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar or sweetened whipped cream.

title: smores that crunch
directions: Place 2 graham cracker squares on microwave safe plate; top each square with one marshmallow.
Microwave for 10 to 15 seconds, or until marshmallow expands. Top each marshmallow with 1 candy bar square and remaining graham cracker square.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: deluxe lemon bars
directions: Beat in blender or with mixer the eggs, sugar and lemon juice until thick and smooth.
Then add flour and baking powder and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onions and salt.
Cover with water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Combine other ingredients.
Bring to a hard boil. Add squash mixture. Bring to a second boil.
Pack in a jar and seal.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add dissolved yeast and buttermilk.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 400°.

title: orange ice
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in same. Add juices.
Freeze.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon pieces in nonstick skillet.
Add onion and fry until onion is clear.
Add entire ingredients including grease into beans; add barbecue sauce.
Stir well.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamsicle salad(light)
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple and oranges (both undrained) in casserole or flat glass dish; leave until set.
Combine and whip skim milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip, then spread on top of jello fruit mixture.
Add grated cheese to top, if desired.

title: apple oatmeal crisp
directions: Slice apples very thin into a greased pie or cake pan.
Mix together oats, sugar and flour; sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add taco seasoning mix.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread one layer of tortilla chips.
Top with 1/3 of meat, 1/2 of refried beans, 1/2 of sour cream and 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat in same proportions.
Top with remaining meat and cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with salsa.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In deep pan, mix brown sugar, white Karo syrup and peanut butter.
Stir often.
Bring to a bubbling boil and remove from burner.
Add one cup at a time, coconut and 6 cups corn flakes (or 8 cups of the cereal).
Spoon and press into buttered 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 to 24 squares.

title: texas bonbons
directions: Melt oleo; pour over pecans.
Add sifted powdered sugar, coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
Shape into small balls; cool in refrigerator.

title: polish mistake
directions: Brown meats in separate skillets; drain well.
Combine meats, cheese and seasonings.
Remove from heat; stir until cheese melts. Spread on rye slices.
Freeze on cookie sheets and place in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for 17 minutes. May garnish with sliced olives or mushrooms.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of glass dish.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
(You may not want to use the whole jar.) Put cooked shrimp over the cocktail sauce.
Sprinkle green onions over shrimp.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar over onions.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften Cheddar and cream cheeses to room temperature.
Mix with butter, olives and Tabasco.
Chill.
Form into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: meat casserole
directions: Pour soup over meat, then add wine.
Do not stir.
Bake in covered casserole undisturbed for 4 hours at 275°.
Good served over Chinese noodles.
To any leftovers, add cooked vegetables for a quick beef stew.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix altogether and put into a greased 8 x 8 inch pan. Bake 350°F. for 45 minutes. Serve hot!

title: rhubarb pecan muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased muffins pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: santa mousse fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese together over low heat or double boiler.
Add sugar, cocoa and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts. Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut in pieces.

title: clam pie dip
directions: Mix all the above in 9 inch pie pan. Over top sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; over top of that put Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Amounts may vary according to taste.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; save liquid.
Pour milk over bread crumbs and stand 5 minutes.
Add flaked salmon, egg, onion, liquid, lemon juice, parsley and seasoning.
Spoon into oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine and chill in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chocolate bars in heavy gauge saucepan.
Melt over very low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Set aside.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch pan. Pour soup, rice and cumin in pan.
Stir slightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: braised beef
directions: In an electric skillet or Dutch oven, heat oil; add meat and brown lightly. Add 1 1/2 cups water, onion, apple, salt and pepper to meat. Cover; simmer over low heat for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Add potatoes and cook covered 10 minutes.
Arrange cabbage wedges around meat and cook for 30 minutes.

Pour tomatoes over meat and heat thoroughly. Remove cabbage and potatoes to serving dish. In small bowl, blend cornstarch with 1 tablespoon water; stir into meat. Simmer until sauce is thickened. Add to serving dish of potatoes and cabbage.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as package directs. Drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender, about 4 to 5 minutes. Mix Cheez Whiz, soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 (1/2 quart) casseroles.
Cook, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.
If frozen, bake 30 minutes longer.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix. Use crushed ice.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Boil squash in small amount of water with salt and pepper and sugar.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle more grated cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh spinach and strawberry salad
directions: In a 4-quart bowl, place the torn spinach, strawberries and green onions.
Place a cover on the bowl and chill for up to 2 hours.
Measure the oil; add the lemon or lime juice and shake well.
Chill.
Shake the dressing again and pour over the spinach-strawberry mixture.
Top with walnuts and, if desired, sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Shape into flat rectangle on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place in glass baking dish. Microwave on Roast for 25 to 30 minutes to to 140 degrees internal temperature.
Combine brown sugar, mustard, and catsup in bowl, blending well.
Pour over meat loaf.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: chicken and pasta marinara
directions: In a large pot, saute garlic in oil.
Add next 6 ingredients. Stir crushed tomatoes.
Add sauce, simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
After 10 minutes add cheese.
Stir.
Cook pasta according to directions.
Add chicken to sauce, uncooked, at the end, 4 minutes.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add yeast and dissolve.
Combine other ingredients and let stand 10 minutes.
Knead dough.
Make out rolls and bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cover and heat candy coating in heavy saucepan over very low heat until soft, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir until smooth and creamy.
Mix in peanut butter; stir in cereal until well coated.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: rice dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Decorate with maraschino cherries. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: banana split salad
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature.
Mix sugar, then add fruit (use whole box of berries with juice).
Stir in nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
It will keep for quite some time.
Keep frozen.

directions: First, use care; get

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake crust for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce temperature to 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Add cherry pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly on top of fruit. Spread cut up margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle walnuts on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Watch toward end of time to avoid burning. Can be topped with whipped cream or Cool Whip after cake is thoroughly cooled.

title: hamburger chow mein casserole
directions: Mix and place in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: mom's white cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Add baking powder and sift once more.
Cream sugar and butter thoroughly.
Add flour and water, beating well after each addition of flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Flavor to taste.

title: easy lemon cheese pie
directions: In blender, cut into cubes, whole lemon (remove seeds and part of rind); blend for one minute with 1/2 cup water.
Add 1 cup sugar, 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup margarine.
Blend thoroughly; pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell; bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve at room temperature with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes.
Add small amount of milk to moisten.
Add American cheese (finely cut), bread (finely cut), butter, parsley flakes, green pepper (finely cut) and onion (finely cut).
Add salt.
Place in large casserole.
Cover top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: garlic steak
directions: Combine steak sauce, oil, pepper and garlic.
Place steak in plastic bag.
Add marinade, turning to coat. Close bag securely and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour, turning once. Remove steak from marinade.
Place on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 4-inches from heat.
Broil 15 to 18 minutes to desired doneness, turning once.

title: fried chicken gravy
directions: After chicken has cooked, remove from pan.
Pour off all but 5 tablespoons fat.	On low heat, add onions and saute.
Add flour; stir until brown.
Add water or milk and stir until smooth. Add salt and pepper.
Simmer on low for about 10 minutes.
Gravy will be creamier if milk is used.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and butter.
Cook on low until begins to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Beat until thickens and pour out onto greased pan.
The thinner you can pour it the better off you are.

title: peanut butter dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of milk as directed on package.
Use large mixing bowl.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Set aside.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine dry ingredients and store in covered container.

title: ruby red sparkle
directions: Mix juices and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: *Made from 1 stick melted margarine and 1 round of Ritz crackers.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Cut toast in quarters into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast. Pour mixture over toast.
Let stand 10 minutes, then sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except linguini.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Cook linguini.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
Combine linguini and artichoke mixture.
Cover and chill. Toss before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread rolls in 11 x 15-inch or larger jelly roll pan, brush on beaten egg and bake according to directions on the can.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine meat, 1 cup picante sauce, oats, 1/2 cup tortilla chips, onion, egg, cumin, garlic powder and salt. Mix well.
Press firmly into 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: branham's marinated shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp until pink; remove shell and devein.
Cover with dressing and vinegar.
Add peppers and onion.
Cover tightly and refrigerate two days before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook (boil) the chicken until done.
Save water.
Pull chicken off into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; be sure to save water after done for more broth.
Combine Cheez Whiz, both soups, chicken and spaghetti in large bowl.
Put into pan half of it.
Grate 1/2 Cheddar cheese on top.
Put rest of mixture on top of that.
Add grated cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
(Add broth from chicken to mixture in the bowl to make it slightly runny.)

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, sugar and oil in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats, cornflakes and chocolate chips.

title: baked chicken extraordinaire
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Place in browning bag.
Add vegetables (mixed) around chicken.
Seal bag and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Check for tenderness.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone chicken and save broth. Cook spaghetti in broth until done and add cheese while this is hot.
Saute onions and bell pepper with oleo in microwave 12 minutes, then let stand covered with Saran Wrap for 5 minutes. Add this to spaghetti.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes that you have cut up real good and add chicken.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut biscuits apart.
Roll each biscuit in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place in pie plate and bake 15 minutes.

title: drop doughnut balls
directions: Mix sugar, milk and egg.
Add melted shortening.
Mix and add flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to liquid and mix lightly.
Drop by teaspoon into hot (375°) fat.
Cook until brown. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: good biscuit mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator in tightly covered dish.
Use as needed.
Bake at 450°.

title: hotshot chicken
directions: In a large glass bowl, combine salsa, mustard and lime juice. Mix well.
Pound each chicken breast half lightly to flatten the thickest part so the pieces will cook evenly.
Add chicken pieces to salsa mixture, turning each piece to coat.
(If you have time, let the chicken marinate at least 30 minutes or refrigerate overnight.)

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.

title: butternut cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl, adding flour last.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake in cold oven at 250° for 1 hour, then at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: gratin potatoes
directions: Mix milk, cream, salt and pepper and bring to a boil; pour mixture into a 10-inch baking dish over the sliced potatoes and top with the cheeses. Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender and the top has browned. Serve hot!

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Mix
together flour, baking powder and	salt.
Add
1/4 cup milk and mix well.	Add the rest of the milk a little at a time. Knead the dough until it is soft.
Cover
the
bowl and let it stand for 15 minutes.
Make balls 2
or 3 inches across and
roll them into pancakes 1/4 inch thick.	Poke
holes
in them with a fork.
Melt shortening in
skillet.
Fry
pancakes until brown and turn over and brown on other side.

title: gelene's braised sirloin tips(heart smart)
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a large heavy skillet.
Add consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion powder.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch and water, stir gradually into the stew. Cook, stirring constantly until gravy thickens and boils, cook 1 minute more.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon and sugar pancakes
directions: Mix flour and egg; add water to desired thickness.
Add cinnamon and sugar to desired taste.
Put oil in skillet until it fills the bottom.
Let get hot, then pour pancake mix, to size desired, into skillet.
Let brown on bottom, turn over and let bottom brown.
Keep oil in skillet.

title: drumsticks
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Brown chicken in 1/2 stick margarine. Drain.
Pour 1/2 cup marinade over chicken and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Add more marinade, if needed.

title: southern biscuits(club member: ashley wilson)
directions: Pour flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl. Cut in shortening thoroughly until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in buttermilk. Knead and roll dough a little less than half an inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ramen salad
directions: Mix cabbage, chicken and ramen noodles, add onions.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line cake pan with crackers.
Mix pudding and milk together and fold in the Cool Whip until mixed well.
Pour half the mixture over the graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and rest of pudding mixture.
Put a layer of graham crackers on top, then ice it with milk chocolate icing.
Let set 4 hours.

title: sausage jambalaya a la richard
directions: Saute white onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add sausage; cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper, if desired, or just salt and pepper to taste. When meat is cooked, add to 4 cups of cooked rice.
If dry, add more margarine.

title: three bean frank bake
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach until thawed and separate.
Dice cheese and butter; beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamed crab
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour until blended and smooth.
Slowly add cream, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add Tabasco and sherry.
Cook over very low heat for 3 minutes.
Add crabmeat and salt to taste.
Cook only until heated.
Serve over toast or rice.

title: almond joy candy
directions: Mix together coconut, milk and almonds.
Refrigerate for at least one hour.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Roll mixture into balls and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves, in hollowed out tomatoes or as a side dish with other vegetables.

title: beef a la mode
directions: Rub meat, to coat, with bacon.
Then coat on all sides with seasoned flour.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven; brown the meat on all sides.
Add 1 cup of water and onions, cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours until meat is tender.
Add more water during cooking as necessary.
Add the carrots, potatoes and peas about 20 minutes before the meat is done.
Put meat on platter.
Arrange vegetables around it.
Cover with brown gravy.

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix all together well.
Form into rolls.
Put in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake on rack.
I use my broiler pan at 300°
for 1 hour.
Remove plastic wrap before baking.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Take out of oven and crumble potato chips on top.
(You can also sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.)
Then bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
You can mix milk and sour cream and pour over other ingredients.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Boil lima beans, mustard and soda for 7 minutes.
Drain. Cover with cold water.
Add salt.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Drain. Mix cream and brown sugar.
Add to beans.
Bake in casserole at 275° for 3 hours.

title: yogurt dip
directions: A bowl of soup is a familiar sight to the Pennsylvania Dutchman.
It has always been thus.
Lots of soup with plenty of stuff in it.
No broth or bouillon, thank you.
Our cream soups we fill with rivvels, noodles, butter balls, dough balls, crackers, pretzels, and even popcorn.
There are a few that we call "Poorman's Soups":

brown flour soup and the popular rivvel soup. When the first settlers came here, these were important to the housewife in the months before the ground could be cleared and tilled for growing vegetables.
Later, as meat and vegetables became plentiful, a great variety of soups were created.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve hot with dipper-size Fritos.

title: spiced cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in cranberries, orange, apple, walnuts, cinnamon and cloves.
Pour into a 4-cup ring mold.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.
To serve, unmold onto serving dish. Garnish as desired.

title: old fashioned blueberry pie
directions: Gently mix berries, 1/3 cup flour, salt and sugar; set aside. Mix milk and oil.
Stir into flour until it forms a ball (a food processor works great).
Divide dough in half and roll between sheets of waxed paper.
Peel off top piece of paper and turn into 9-inch pie pan.
Peel off other piece of paper.
Spoon blueberry mixture into pastry shell.
Dot with butter.
Repeat pastry procedure and gently place on top of pie.
Trim off excess and fold edges under.
Cut slits in top of crust and bake at 425° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Place strips of foil over edges of crust to prevent overbrowning.
Serves 6.

title: catalina vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl and beat in salad dressing with a fork until desired consistency and flavors are attained.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado and mix with sour cream and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.
If serving later, store covered in refrigerator with avocado pits on top.
This prevents browning, serve with taco corn chips.

title: zucchini - hungarian style
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Cook for 10 minutes the zucchini, water, vinegar, salt, paprika and dill leaves.
In another pan, brown the onion and flour mixture in the bacon fat or margarine. Mix small amounts of zucchini mixture into the browned mixture until all is combined and smooth.
Cool mixture a bit, then add the sour cream.

title: spinach roll
directions: Roll out dough in a large circle.
Place spinach over dough. Sprinkle both cheeses, garlic, salt and pepper over spinach. Drizzle oil over spinach.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Fold ends under.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Filling can also be sliced pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Measure crushed corn flakes into shallow dish or pan; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg and milk slightly.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter. Coat with cereal.
Place in single layer, skinned side up in greased or foil lined shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (until tender).
Do not cover, turn chicken while baking.

title: pepsi cake
directions: Cook in Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Spread nuts on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix, pudding, Pepsi, oil, eggs and water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour on top of nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Melt butter; crush Ritz crackers.
Mix together and set aside.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: Beat egg in 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Stir in corn, milk, green peppers, onion, sugar and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with remaining crumbs and paprika.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix ingredients together and pour into pan.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush a 10-inch round casserole or souffle dish with oil.
Arrange a layer of squash slices evenly on the bottom of the dish.
Top with a layer of onion; sprinkle with salt, pepper and salad herbs.
Dot with slices of Cheddar.
Repeat the layers, alternating the Havarti and Cheddar.
Finish with layer of cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 35 minutes.
Remove foil; continue baking until squash is tender and cheese is bubbly, 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sourdough starter bread
directions: Scald milk and add margarine.
Cool to lukewarm; add to dry ingredients.
Add starter and flour.
Knead until elastic.
Grease bowl and place dough in it, turning it to coat top.
Let double. Make into loaves and double again.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes. Coat top with shortening when removing from oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together with hands until well blended.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: lemon-blueberry bread
directions: In large bowl, mix margarine, sugar and lemon juice. Beat in eggs. In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture to margarine mixture alternately with the milk, stirring just enough to blend. Stir in blueberries and grated rind. Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about an hour and 10 minutes. Cool and store, foil wrapped, for one day before slicing.

title: spanish olive salad
directions: Toss and put up in empty olive bottles of jars.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook in crock-pot for about 2 hours on low heat or simmer in pan for 45 minutes.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add cheese cut into small pieces.
When melted, slowly wisk in beer.
Add spices and beaten egg very slowly.
Great over toast points and/or asparagus.

title: texas cake with frosting
directions: Mix together flour and sugar; then set aside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool. Prepare pudding as directed.
Crumble cake (half) in the bottom of a pretty punch bowl.
Spread half of pudding on cake layer in order, half of pineapple, half of pie filling, half of Cool Whip and half of nuts.
Repeat and refrigerate.
This should be made a day before serving.

title: david's one skillet breakfast
directions: In a large skillet add sausage, diced pepper and onions, cook until sausage is browned.
In a large bowl beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour eggs over into skillet and add cheese, stirring well until eggs are done.
Serve with toast.

title: mock turkey casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Dilute both cans of soup with milk instead of water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Add soup with water.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter; sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sue reeves' six minute pecan pie
directions: Mix
and stir in bowl the eggs, syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Stir
in	nuts.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: german pinwheels(open faced sandwiches)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a baking sheet.
Mix meat, eggs, onions, parsley, bread and pepper.
Place meat mixture on a sheet of plastic wrap and flatten evenly with a wet spatula to a rectangle (10 x 15-inch).

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1 c. sugar in iron skillet. Mix other ingredients in sauce pan to heat, then add to sugar in skillet. Mix well; then pour into pie shells. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: dill casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water. Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast mixture. Add flour to form a stiff dough. Beat well after each addition. Cover. Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size. Stir down (or punch down). Turn into a well-greased 2-quart casserole dish. Let rise again until light. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown. Brush with melted butter while hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put the soup, milk and cream cheese in a blender and blend. Combine with the potatoes and put into a greased baking dish. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
About 5 to 10 minutes before done, uncover and put grated cheese on them.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pyrex dish with whole graham crackers; spread 1/2 of pudding mixture on top.
Add another layer of crackers and remaining pudding.
Add another layer of crackers.
Spread with frosting and refrigerate.

title: myrtle's quick candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Add corn flakes; stir until all are coated with mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes a lot.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Cook berries and 2 cups of water about 10 minutes.
Put through sieve to make a smooth pulp.
Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Pour into freezing tray.
Freeze until firm, stirring several times.
Good at holidays to accompany ham or turkey.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Combine dates, margarine, sugar and eggs in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until dates are dissolved, about 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend shortening and sugars; stir in vanilla.
Add the beaten egg and peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Sift the dry ingredients together 3 times and stir into peanut butter mixture. Shape into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pat's punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake in bottom of a punch bowl.
Mix together Cool Whip, sugar, sour cream and milk.
Pour over cake and mix together.
Mix strawberries and glaze together and pour on top.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Combine cheese, milk, margarine and salt; heat until cheese melts.
Stir in hash browns.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread sour cream and bacon bits on top. Continue cooking 10 minutes more.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Grate cucumbers.
Squeeze water out.
Grate onion; mix with cucumber.
Add cream cheese to vegetables; mix well.
Salt and pepper.

title: monkey bread
directions: With scissors, cut into fourths.
Roll each quarter in sugar and cinnamon, coating well.
Place in a greased tube pan in layers.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuit quarters.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Make into balls and place in baking pan.

title: lemon-herb chicken(4 servings and low-fat)
directions: Trim all visible fat from chicken.
Combine oil, tarragon and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken, covering all pieces.
Toss chicken in marinade to assure even coverage.
Marinate for 30 minutes, turning at least twice.
Arrange chicken on broiler pan; place under broiler, broiling each side for approximately 5 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink inside.
Serve.

title: whole wheat banana muffins
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to banana.
Mix alternately with hot water.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 325° for 20 minutes for regular muffins or 17 minutes for miniature muffins.

title: shrimp salad ono nui
directions: Cut shrimp in bite-size pieces, halves or thirds.
Toss with pineapple chunks and celery into a bowl.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add carrots and dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread 1 tube crescent rolls on a small cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes, until browned.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix chopped veggies in a bowl.
Sprinkle veggies on top of cream cheese. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: caramel custard
directions: Butter 5 to 6 custard cups.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
In a heavy saucepan, heat 1/2 cup sugar until brown.
Pour melted sugar into custard cups.
Heat, but do not boil, milk.
If you want rich custard, use 1-1/2 cups milk and 1/2 cup heavy cream.
Blend eggs, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Blend in milk.
Pour into custard cups. Set in pan in 1 inch of water.
Bake 1 hour or until silver knife inserted in custard comes out clean.
Chill.
Invert onto serving plates.
Top with a dab of whipping cream lightly sweetened with powdered sugar and flavored with vanilla.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Brown
chicken
in Crisco in frying pan.
Pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer on low heat for 45 minutes
until
tender, stirring occasionally.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: cranberry tapioca
directions: Mix tapioca and salt.
Add water; bring to boiling over direct heat and stir constantly. Cool.
Add orange juice, rind and cranberry sauce.
Fold in cream.
Pour into sherbet glasses and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wrapped wieners
directions: You will also need 1 box of toothpicks.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the oats in boiling water.
Let stand 45 minutes.
Cream together the brown sugar, white sugar and butter. Add oats and beat well. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix in bowl the chicken, Veg-All (drained), cream of chicken and cream of celery.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish or pan and spread it out.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and put crushed chips on top.
Put back in oven.
Turn to 450° and bake until chips are brown.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix this well.	Use 3 teaspoons of Tang and tea mixture with 1 cup boiling water to make 1 cup of Russian tea.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top of rice. Mix other ingredients together and pour over rice and chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kick-off burgers
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Brown the beef and onion.
Stir in vegetable soup, undiluted.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Blend in salt, flour and sour cream. Serve over buns, toast or rice and sprinkle cheese on top.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: people having garden problems
directions: Some can be
prevented	by using wood ashes, sulfur and Epsom salts.
It	does
not
have
to
be
accurate
measures. Garden sulfur and Epsom
salts
can be bought in 30 pound bags at big savings, and
it keeps if you have a tight container to put it in. Can also be used heavily to sprinkle on top of the rows once they are
covered.
Good for root maggots and keeps carrots, beets and radishes from being wormy.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to directions.
Add cream cheese and mix until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate until set.
Top with favorite pie filling and serve.

title: zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch slices and thinly slice onion.
Cook squash and onion in butter in skillet until tender.
Add salt, tomato sauce and oregano.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts, 30 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix sugar, Butter Buds, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add cornflakes. Mix pie filling with extract.
Pour pie filling into 1-quart dish. Top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
Serve topped with frozen yogurt.

title: quick peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Scoop dough into rounded tablespoonfuls and roll in sugar. Cook as package directs.
Take from oven and quickly press a kiss into center, pushing down firmly.
This is good to keep on hand for unexpected company.

title: crab spaghetti
directions: Cook the spaghetti in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain.
Heat the soup and keep stirring until smooth.
Add the butter and milk.
When hot, remove from fire and stir in grated cheese.
Combine this cheese sauce with spaghetti, crab meat and season with pepper.
Place in a shallow greased casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in hot oven.

title: microwave quickie fudge
directions: In 2-quart bowl, melt butter.
Combine powdered sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and butter.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir to blend ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts; blend well.
Line pie plate evenly with wax paper.
Pour fudge into plate and chill until firm.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the oatmeal and the peanut butter; cook over medium heat until boiling.
Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add the 1/2 cup of peanut butter and the 3 cups of oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or buttered dish.
Allow to cool.
If you like, you may add raisins to this also.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Blend in remaining ingredients to make stiff dough.
Thoroughly chill dough.
Roll out very thin on well floured board.
Cut as desired and place on greased cookie sheet.
May be sprinkled with cookie decorations before or after baking.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: hickory or walnut cake
directions: Fill the cake pan with a layer of the cake, then a layer of raisins upon that, then scatter nuts until the pan is 2/3 full. Line the tins with well-buttered paper and bake in a steady, but not quick oven.
This is most excellent.

title: grammie's chocolate cocoa cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a medium oven for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and melted butter.
Add eggs, cocoa and salt, mixing well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: chip beef chicken
directions: Place a layer of dried beef in bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast in a slice of bacon and place on top of dried beef.
Combine soup and sour cream; spread over all. Cover and bake 3 hours at 275°.
Uncover and bake another 45 minutes.

title: burger bundles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix meat, soup mix, egg, pepper, water and bread crumbs.
Press onto bottom of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Prick meat mixture with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or to desired doneness.
Drain.
Place Velveeta slices over meat.
Bake 1 minute or until Velveeta begins to melt. Cut into 24 squares.

title: 4 bean hot dish
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces.
Fry together with onion until bacon is brown. Stir all ingredients together. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix water and Jell-O; then add cream cheese.
Slowly blend until smooth.
Mix Dream Whip until whipped, then add sugar, beating until stiff.
Add Jell-O mixture and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cool 2 or 3 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt sugar, oleo and 1/2 cup water; cool until lukewarm.
Add the yeast dissolved in 1/4 cup or less lukewarm water, the beaten egg, 1/2 cup water, 1 teaspoon salt and 3 cups flour.
Mix together until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator about 1 hour before baking time.
Shape into rolls and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa. Stir in milk and margarine. Blend in nuts. Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan that has been lightly sprayed with Pam. Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over top of batter. Pour hot water over top of batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom. Invert squares of pudding on dessert plates and spoon sauce over top.

title: uncle ben's mexican rice
directions: Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Then let simmer until all the water is out.
Then sit out for awhile in another container or casserole dish.

title: monte crisco sandwiches
directions: Fill jars to 1 1/2-inch from top of jar.
Place in oven for 45 minutes.
Place lids on jars, cool on white cloth.
Do not allow lids to touch.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Make sure to drain spinach well.
Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper together.
In large casserole, layer potatoes and soup mixture.
Add sausage and cheese.
Repeat layer again, ending with sausage.
Dot with butter and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with cheese slices last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown, meat, onion and green pepper.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Microwave chicken 6 to 8 minutes on High; set aside.
Cook onions and garlic in butter; add flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook on stove top for 30 minutes.
Add chicken; heat thoroughly.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Put noodles in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Brown the ground beef and onions.
Add the tomato soup, garlic salt, onion salt, pepper and oregano to ground beef and pour over noodles.
Cover with Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Put fresh or canned mushrooms on top, if desired.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: strawberry brunch bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients. In a large bowl, beat eggs thoroughly and add to Crisco. Slowly add the sifted mixture, alternating with the strawberries (include juice from packages). Add vanilla and strawberry flavoring. Add the black walnuts; mix thoroughly. Spray pans with Pam and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, depending on oven and size of bread pans.

title: ham steak
directions: Marinate ham with combined ingredients overnight.
Grill ham steak 10 minutes per side.
Delicious!

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add in layers the remaining ingredients in the order given.
Pour condensed milk over all ingredients.
Do not mix.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° for approximately 3 hours.
Cover with foil the last 1/2 hour.

title: savory green beans
directions: Coat
a
large non-stick skillet with cooking spray and place over
medium
heat.
Add
onion and saute until tender. Add remaining
ingredients and cover and simmer 15 minutes or until string
beans are
tender.	Yields about 6 servings and only 36 calories per serving.

title: fresh pesto
directions: In a food processor, grind basil and garlic.
Add nuts and cheeses, then slowly add the olive oil.
Blend to desired consistency, adding more olive oil if needed.
Spoon into small jars and seal with melted butter.
Yields about 2 cups.
Pesto can also be placed and frozen in ice trays.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Place all in a large bowl.
Mix the dressing in a container with lid or use the jar from the green olives.

title: merry cheese cake
directions: Combine flour, butter, nuts and brown sugar.
Pat into small cupcake holders.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Add juice from asparagus.
You may add milk to make more sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: In small bowl with electric mixer, beat eggs slightly.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans. Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
(Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edge.)
Cool; if desired serve with whipped cream.

title: apricot-pineapple marmalade
directions: Wash and grind dried apricots.
Add and boil until thickened and clear, crushed pineapple, lemon and sugar, stirring constantly.
Pour into hot jars; seal.
Yields 2 pints marmalade.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Add zucchini and onions to the boiling liquid.
Bring to a boil again.
Pack in pint jars and seal at once.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds and cornflakes.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Remove from oven and top with buttered corn flakes and almonds.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cheesy nachos
directions: Arrange tortilla chips on a 10-inch plate.
Place remaining ingredients in a plastic bag and shake to mix well.
Sprinkle mixture over the chips.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 3 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts, rotating plate 2 or 3 times during cooking.

title: date nut bars
directions: Melt butter, sugar and dates.
Cook slow for 10 minutes; stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Let cool.
Roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in butter.
Drain off excess. Combine sauce and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Skim off any excess fat and pour sauce over chicken.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Makes a double batch.

title: large banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip. Mix together the cream cheese and condensed milk and then beat together with pudding mixture. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding, then chill.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to the boiling water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Over low heat, make a white sauce of milk, flour and margarine, by combining melted margarine with flour and then slowly adding milk.
Heat until it thickens, then add shredded cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
When melted, add cooked vegetables and water.
Do not drain.
Add corn and heat to liking.
Do not boil!
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a slice in stem end of peppers, so it will stand up.
Cut a slice off top, so to remove seeds and then thoroughly wash.
Bring salted water to a boil and add peppers, so to cook for 5 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beef, garlic and onion in skillet until onion is tender.
Drain off fat and stir in salt, rice and half the tomato sauce.
Heat mixture for several minutes and remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers with the mixture and stand upright in a baking dish.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over hte top of peppers and bake covered for 45 minutes.
Bake uncovered for 15 more minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned. Drain off.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and simmer thoroughly. Serve on warm buns.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: alaskan fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits well.
Mix all ingredients together well. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese, then mushrooms over the chicken.
Combine soups and spread over chicken.
Add the melted oleo and hot water to stuffing mix and spread this over the soup layer.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours uncovered.
Note:
You can easily use 8 pieces of chicken if you do not wish to use just breasts of chicken.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes and add Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: "amy's" beef soup
directions: Brown meat lightly and drain.
Add vegetables to meat with water, gravy mix, barley and seasoning.
Pressure cook 15 minutes or simmer 45 to 50 minutes.

title: drunk chicken
directions: Brown fryer in oil.
Remove from frypan and place in baking pan.
Add and melt butter to remaining oil in frypan.
Add wine, garlic, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Pour over chicken and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Baste occasionally.

title: dilly lime salad
directions: Drain the pineapple well, reserving all syrup.
Add syrup to gelatin in a 2-quart saucepan. Stir in water, seasoned salt and dill weed.
Heat mix to boiling, stirring constantly, to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Chill until mix thickens to consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Blend in cottage cheese. Fold in pineapple. Pour into 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold onto crisp salad greens to serve.

title: mostaccioli(beef and noodles)
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Simmer sauce and spices. Add meat (cook noodles).
Layer noodles, cheese and meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (takes much longer if refrigerated).

title: simple chicken soup
directions: Place all of the ingredients into a large soup pot with enough water to cover.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Skim off the scum, re-cover, lower heat and simmer for 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: transfer ink
directions: Number 1:
Wallpaper paste, colored with powdered paint and made thin enough to spread, will not run and is easily washed off later.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 box pudding, eggs, oil, Club soda and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in tube pan 45 to 55 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Mix 1 box pudding and 1 envelope Dream Whip with 1 1/4 cups milk. Beat until it holds a peak.
Frost cooled cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh peach sauce
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, mix peaches, sugar and orange juice. Place over high heat and stir until boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Serve warm on pound cake or chill the sauce to make up parfaits.

title: iced almonds
directions: Stir almonds, sugar and butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Stir until almonds are toasted, about 15 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread nuts on foil or Teflon cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into well greased deep dish pie shell.
Pour drained peaches over mixture.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice; pour over peaches and mixture.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: my mother's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until straw, when inserted in cake, comes out clean.

title: mama's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 325°.
(Bake slightly less than 1 hour if using an oblong cake pan.)

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and boil a few minutes.
Pour over meat.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs one at a time and beat. Add flour, about 1/2 cup at a time, beating after each addition. Add lemon extract. Fold in 7-Up and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: hot ground turkey and salad
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add ground turkey; brown.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, sherry and vinegar.
Add to meat mixture, stirring until thick.
Add water chestnuts.
Put meat mixture on top of rice or Chinese noodles, then top with salad.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and peel. Put in gallon jar. Boil sugar, vinegar, spices, onions and juice about 1 minute. Pour over eggs and refrigerate 2 days before eating.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in
hot
water.
Take from fire and add sherbet, working fast, have well mixed and partially set.
Add marshmallows,
pineapple
and
oranges
last.
Fold in whipped cream.
Does better if chilled overnight or about 6 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Try to handle as little as possible. Roll out pastry.
Makes 1 single pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate a few hours.

title: easy chocolate chip pie
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and chips.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, pecans and coconut.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter with Cheez Whiz or Velveeta cheese.
Mix cooked broccoli and cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 1/2 stick melted butter with crackers.
Sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana and chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil.
Add oil, beating slowly.
Use this dressing over Chinese cabbage or lettuce with sliced bananas.

title: maple walnut cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add well beaten egg yolks, then milk and flour which has been sifted with salt and baking powder, alternately.
Then add vanilla and walnuts and bake for 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: eggplant skillet
directions: Cook beef or turkey, onion and celery until meat is browned. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and oregano. Season eggplant slices with salt and pepper.
Arrange on top of meat sauce.
Cover; simmer until eggplant is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese and dried beef casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole.
Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnite.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and sour or buttermilk. Sift soda, flour and salt.
Add vanilla and rhubarb.
Top with nuts, white sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Some ovens may only take 30 minutes.

title: ham sauce
directions: Combine with garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and celery seed to taste.

title: pink punch
directions: May mix directly in punch bowl. Add lots of crushed ice.
Add lemon slices, if desired.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Crush crackers.
Combine sugar, walnuts and baking powder, mixing well together.
Then beat eggs, adding milk and vanilla. Stir the mixture into this.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: brisket by woody
directions: Put first 2 ingredients in stewer, heat and dissolve.
Pour over brisket.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn after 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Slice and cook several hours more.
Cooks very tender.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring fruit juice and sugar to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add lemon juice and let cool.
Combine fruit, thawed orange juice (undiluted) and the boiled juice.
Stir well.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Grease 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Line bottoms of pans with wax paper; grease wax paper.
Flour wax paper and sides of pans. Set aside.
Beat butter and shortening at medium speed of an electric mixer until soft and creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour and soda; add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; peel off wax paper.
Cool on wire racks.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.
Yield:
One 3-layer cake.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Mix sour cream with spaghetti sauce.
Add to ravioli (fried or canned).
Cut thawed broccoli spears lengthwise.
Place layer of spears on bottom of lightly oiled 13-inch oblong pan (save some for garnish).
Pour ravioli
mixture over broccoli.
Garnish with remaining broccoli.
Sprinkle 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese over all.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. johnson's swedish brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add melted butter; mix well (batter will be thick).
Add eggs and almond extract; mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until nice and brown.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour over butter.
Add pie fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zenobia bryant's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven
to 450°.	Cook pumpkin.
Mix all ingredients in order
given.
Bake
15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking 45
minutes.
Whipped cream can be used to top off, if desired.

title: fluffy uncooked frosting
directions: Mix sugar, egg white and cream of tartar, then add boiling water.
Beat with electric mixer at highest speed until stiff (about 5 minutes).
This will hold shape and will not become crusty.
It can be stored in refrigerator.
Also good on puddings, pies and short cakes.
Enough for 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: japanese pear salad
directions: Mix together salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and oil for dressing. Pour over lettuce and pears.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine egg whites, bread crumbs, tomatoes, chili peppers, olives, onions, cumin and pepper.
Add turkey or beef; mix well. Place mixture into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Transfer to a platter.
Top with
cheese and let set for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: herren's sweet rolls
directions: Scald milk in heavy saucepan.
Add butter, sugar and salt. Cool.
Soften yeast in water and add to mixture.
Add flour, a cup at a time, and beat.
Turn onto floured board and let rest 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth.
Place in buttered bowl and cover with cloth until doubled in size.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into 8-inch squares.
Brush with butter.

title: crab ball
directions: Open crab meat and drain well.
Soften cream cheese with fork. Add onion and horseradish.
Fold in crab meat.
Shape into ball. Chill.
Arrange on lettuce leaf on tray.
Serve with crackers.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt before adding.
Cream sugar and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, soda and salt.
Alternate with sour cream.
Add vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until done.

title: cherry dessert
directions: In a slightly greased 9 x 11-inch pan, spread a can of crushed pineapple (juice and all).
Next, sprinkle pecans evenly.
Add dry cake mix and sprinkle evenly.
Then pour melted butter over all. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one by one, beating well.
Add flour and spice to mixture.
Mix soda and buttermilk and stir until fluffy.
Add to batter.
Add vanilla and bourbon. Pour over fruit.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, then lower heat to 300° or 325°.

title: black bean and corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Stir in oil, lime juice.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Chill and let marinade for several hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Dice or grate potatoes into large bowl.
Season and add other ingredients, saving some cheese for the top.
Mix with a fork. Put into a 2-quart casserole or baking pan.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or longer until bubbly in the center.
Some buttermilk added to the sour cream enhances flavor and moistness.

title: potato-bacon snacks
directions: Cut each bacon slice crosswise into thirds.
Wrap 1 bacon piece around each Tater Tot and secure with toothpick.
Place on broiler grid. Broil approximately 4-inches from flame 5 minutes on each side or until bacon is crisp. Serve hot.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in a tube pan greased and floured.
Mix a glaze of powdered sugar, milk and butter (pouring consistency).
Pour over warm cake.

title: coconut muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine and then eggs together.
Blend in other ingredients.
Divide evenly into 12 greased muffin cups and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed (use only half of batter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan).
Let cake cool.
Then spread on crushed pineapple, juice included.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Soften cream cheese (45 seconds in microwave), then add egg, sugar and beat well.
Stir in the chocolate chips; set aside. Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Fill paper baking cups half full with cocoa mixture.
Spoon heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle each with nuts and a little sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook first five ingredients to soft ball stage (about 25 minutes).
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons oleo, vanilla, powdered sugar and red food coloring.
Stir until thickened.
Pour into buttered pan or drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream well the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Press dough into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares while warm.
Cool, then remove from pan.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Grind peppers and cook all ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Take 1 pint of water and add slowly to 1 cup flour to make a thin paste.
Pour into pepper mixture; boil for 10 minutes and seal in hot jars.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Mix whipped cream, milk and lemon juice together.
Add strawberries.
Cut or tear cake into small pieces.
Pour whipped cream mixture over cake and chill.

title: squirrel country style
directions: Cut squirrel into serving pieces and shake in a paper bag containing seasoned flour to dredge well.
Fry in skillet until golden brown.
Remove squirrel from skillet and pour off all grease except 2 teaspoons.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Return squirrel to skillet; turn on low heat, cover and cook for about 1 hour, until meat almost leaves bone.
Turn squirrel occasionally and baste often.
Serve with grits, hot biscuits and honey.

title: quick batter yeast rolls
directions: In
large
mixing
bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk and water mixture.
Stir in sugar, oil and salt. Add flour and mix well. Spoon
into
greased
muffin
pans.
Bake in a 425° oven about
15 minutes
or
until
brown.
Tops may be brushed with butter before baking if desired.
Yield:
12 to 18 rolls.

title: ham shortcake
directions: Brown ham slightly in fat.
Cook well if uncooked ham is used. Stir in flour; add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in mustard, salt and celery salt; add eggs.
Heat just until hot; stir only to keep from sticking.
Serve over hot split biscuits. Yields 8 servings.

title: corn moussaka
directions: Spread corn in a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole or a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and garlic in a medium skillet; drain off excess fat.
Add flour; cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir in tomato sauce, salt and cinnamon.
Pour this over corn in dish.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: saint joseph's day cream puffs(sfingi di san giuseppe)
directions: Combine
butter,
salt
and water in saucepan; bring to boil. Add
flour
all
at
one time and mix well, until dough leaves side of pan.
Remove from stove and cool a little.
Add eggs,
one at
a
time, mixing well after each addition.
Add sugar, orange and lemon peel; mix thoroughly.

title: gita's chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan on medium heat.
Add garlic and onions. Cook for about 4 minutes.
Add chicken pieces.
Cook on medium heat for 8 minutes.
Then add cut up mushrooms, carrots, tomato, allspice, turmeric powder, salt, pepper and hot pepper.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on low heat, then add the stock.
(The stock can be made by boiling the chicken skin and bones in water.)
Cover with lid and cook for 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Add sugar and lemon juice right before you serve the dish.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet kosher dills
directions: Drain 2 quarts dill pickles and set in ice water overnight. Make syrup with sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Drain ice water from pickles and pour hot syrup mixture over them.
Cover and let set 8 to 10 hours.
Drain syrup mixture from pickles and put back into saucepan.
Add spices and bring back to boil.
Put pickles into jars and pour heated mixture with spices over them making sure pickles are evenly distributed in the jars.
Pickles may be eaten next day.

title: stuffed mushrooms caesar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove and finely chop mushroom stems. In medium bowl, combine dressing, bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and chopped stems.
Fill each mushroom with bread crumb mixture; place in shallow baking dish.
Add water to barely cover bottom and bake 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes about 24 appetizers.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix sour cream and butter thoroughly. Sift flour. Work with butter mixture.
Add water.
Fill small muffin pans and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
These freeze really well.

title: best-ever banana muffins
