directions: Mash bananas with potato masher. Add sugar, egg and melted margarine. Combine dry ingredients and add to banana mixture. Mix only lightly. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time; beat well after adding each.
Stir in milk.
Stir flour and baking powder together.
Stir in egg mixture.
Chill.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend the flour, salt and pepper.
Place 1/3 of potatoes in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the flour mixture.
Repeat the layers, then place third layer of potatoes on top.
Pour hot milk over all, then pour over butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 to 70 minutes longer until tender.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Separate flower buds and short stems from stalks. Cook bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix bacon and other ingredients.
Pour sauce over broccoli salad just prior to serving.
Refrigerate leftovers, if any.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients together, except black olives.
Add after adding Miracle Whip.
(Refrigerate to keep cool.)

title: apricot balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar. Chill overnight.

title: date candy
directions: Cook the dates, margarine and sugar until gooey.
Remove from stove.
Add egg; stir and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Roll in logs.
Roll in coconut. Chill and slice.
Refrigerate.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, pie filling and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half the cake mix in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half the cinnamon and sugar mix. Repeat with rest of cake mix and cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: snow on the mountain punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid following directions.
Chill all beverages. Just before serving, pour Kool-Aid and Coke into punch bowl.
Add ice cream, a scoop at a time.
Pour in ginger ale and serve. Yields 32 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly blend in cream and lemon juice, stirring constantly until the mixture is thickened.
Add lemon peel and simmer for 2 minutes. Add parsley and serve over fish steaks.

title: corny fritters
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and warm water.
In a heavy saucepan, combine cornmeal, sugar, shortening, salt and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring often.
Cool until lukewarm.
In a large bowl, combine corn and eggs.
Stir in yeast mixture and cooled cornmeal mixture.
Mix thoroughly; then stir in 5 cups flour.

title: fudge cake brownies
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo.
Add Hershey's syrup and flour.
Add the eggs one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each egg.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: turkey pot pie(for 12 or more)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Slowly add broth, cream, pepper and salt.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring, until thickened, and stir in vegetables and turkey.
(Can be replaced with chicken.) Top with biscuits or dumplings.
Bake 30 minutes or until biscuits are done all the way through.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the the ground beef. Drain fat. Add seasoning mix.
Stir in the tomato sauce, water and vinegar. Heat thoroughly.

title: bacon and cheese crepes
directions: Saut the onion in butter in a small skillet until tender. Combine the sauteed onion with the cheese, bacon, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise in a bowl and mix well. Divide the mixture into 18 portions. Shape each into a 4-inch log. Place a log on each crepe and roll up to enclose the filling. Arrange seam side down in a greased baking pan. Bake at 375° just until the cheese melts. Cut each crepe into 3 pieces to serve as hors d'oeuvres and arrange on a serving plate. Yield: 54 hors d'oeuvres.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and flour until smooth and creamy. Place dough in wax paper in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on floured board about an eighth-inch thick.
Cut into two-inch squares.
Fill with prune filling, walnuts or preserves.
Roll into crescents.
Bake at 375° until light brown; about 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook first four ingredients together; strain and put back into pot.
Mix sugar, flour and water, then add to the soup.

title: swans down angel food cake
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Add
cup
of
the sugar and sift together 4
times.
Combine
egg
whites,
salt, cream of tartar and flavorings in large bowl.
Beat with flatware whip, eggbeater or at high speed of electric mixer until whites are stiff
enough to hold up in soft peaks but are still moist and glossy.
Add remaining
sugar
in
four additions.
Bake in a 10-inch
tube pan at 375° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan
upside-down
1 hour.
Then
loosen from sides and center tube with knife.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Mix in order given.
Pour into bread tin, greased.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and spoon into wraps.
Wrap and place in baking dish.
Cover with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: beets and onions
directions: Mix the vinegar, sugar, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce together. Add the onion and beets with juice to the mixture. Stir gently to avoid breaking up the beets.
Refrigerate to store. Makes a large amount.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown beef; set aside.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray and set over medium heat.
Add onion and celery; cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are softened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beef, salt and pepper; mix well.
Cook until beef is heated through and vegetables are tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add cheese; melt well, then add noodles and heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, place alternate layers of oysters and crackers, dotting each layer with margarine or butter and sprinkling with small amount of pepper.
End with layer of crumbs.
Add milk until liquid almost reaches top of casserole. Dot with remaining margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° until browned, 45 to 60 minutes. Use all oyster liquid.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: deer jerky
directions: Place a layer of strips in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dab with liquid smoke, garlic salt, sugar and pepper.
Layer until pan is full. Let stand overnight in refrigerator or at least 12 hours.
Dry in oven at 125° until desired texture.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix with rest of ingredients, except breadcrumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with breadcrumbs or crushed cornflakes.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fiesta dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and peppers; mix with tomato paste and sauce.
Grease casserole dish.
Put rice in bottom of dish.
Pour meat mixture over rice.
Mix corn meal mix according to directions.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil, eggs and sugar.
Stir in zucchini and add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Beat.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour 3 (9 x 5-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pecan cutlets
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes.
Shape as thick chops; roll in corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serves six.
Serve with tomato sauce or white sauce or just tomato catsup.

title: party perk
directions: Combine apple juice, cranberry juice cocktail and water in an electric percolator.
Place sugar, cloves, salt and cinnamon in percolator basket.
Perk and serve.
Makes 8 (6 ounce) servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni according to directions on package, drain. While macaroni is cooking, beat the mayonnaise and egg together and then combine with the cottage cheese and cheddar cheese. Combine the cheese mixture with the drained macaroni.
Spread in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add Italian bread crumbs and pats of butter. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Hollow out round bread to use for dip.
Save pieces for dipping.
Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Mix thoroughly and fill hollowed out bread. Refrigerate overnight.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix together and add to the noodles and slaw mixture 1 hour before serving.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Combine molasses and cold water. Sift dry ingredients together, then add alternately with molasses and cold water.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut with favorite cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10-20 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: chutney chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, pineapple, celery, and onion together.
Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, chutney, lemon juice, curry powder, and salt.
Toss with chicken mixture and chill.

title: homemade coffee liqueur(tastes like kahlua)
directions: In 1/2 gallon bottle (with lid), put all ingredients.
Shake well.
After ingredients settle, add water to fill.
Shake once each day for two weeks.
Always store in cool, dark place.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
Heat and stir milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm and shortening almost melts.
Add to flour mixture along with eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.

title: cucumber, tomatoes and onion salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl; toss well and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: best hot dog chili
directions: Brown beef, draining grease well.
Add all ingredients and cook, covered, 2 hours or longer.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar and pretzels.
Bake in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish for 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool. Combine and beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on top of pretzel base.
Prepare jello with boiling water. Add crushed pineapple and strawberries to jello mixture.
Spread on top of Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: mini potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Mix hash browns and eggs.
Spray mini muffin pans with vegetable spray.
Spoon hash brown mixture into the mini muffin pans.
Use mini tart shaper to press hash brown mixture into the bottom and sides of mini muffin pans.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: boston fruit cookies
directions: Blend
together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, sifted flour and
salt.
Combine
stewed
raisins and soda scalded in 1/2 cup raisin juice.
Drop
by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream cheese mixture: Beat together the softened cream cheese and margarine. Add eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth and set aside.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
If desired, cool completely and spread with Brown Butter Glaze.

title: meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in water and mandarin juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring. Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes more, stirring.
Remove from heat. Beat egg yolks, gradually pour in small amount of hot mandarin mixture, stir.
Mix remaining egg yolks with mandarin mixture.
Add mandarin peel and butter, blending well.
Cool 10 minutes and turn into baked pastry shell.
Make meringue by combining 3 egg whites with cream of tartar, beat until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar 1 tablespoon at a time until egg whites are stiff and glossy.
Spoon over filling in pastry shell, spreading so meringue touches edge of crust all around.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Heat together potatoes, onions, California Blend vegetables and bouillon cube in the water.
Heat until vegetables are tender. Then add the cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup; stir until mixed thoroughly.
Add the Velveeta cheese and cook until desired consistency.

title: chicken noodle crunch salad(double recipe)
directions: Mix together chicken, lettuce and green onions. Set aside. Brown almonds, crushed Ramen noodles and sesame seeds in butter. Saute and cool.

title: traditional christmas fudge
directions: *Can use 2 cups (12 ounce package) of butterscotch morsels instead of chocolate morsels.

title: potato filling(mother parkinson, december, 1947)
directions: Mash as many boiled potatoes as desired.
Add onions, cut fine, and fry in a generous amount of butter (add celery, if desired).
Add parsley, rolled or cut fine, just before adding onions and butter to the potatoes, to heat through.
Do not cook too much!!
Mix well.
Add as many beaten raw eggs as desired, depending on the amount of potatoes used.
Season well with salt and pepper (and poultry seasoning, if desired).
Add cut up stale bread (squares or small dices), removing crusts as much as desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the sugar and cream to soft-boil stage. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until a spreading consistency. Pour into 9 x 13 pan to cool. Cut into pieces. Store in airtight container. (Can be put in freezer.)

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In pan, place 1/2 stick butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar; set aside.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over butter and brown sugar.
Cook about 35 minutes at 325°.
In saucepan, put small can of crushed pineapple, 1/2 stick butter, and sugar.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Pour over hot cake.

title: jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Mix in rest of ingredients and put in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Let set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, but not too done.
Partially drain. Mix 1/2 stick of margarine and all the cheese (does not have to be melted) and stir into broccoli.
Pour into greased baking dish. Mix other half of butter (melted) with cracker crumbs.
Spoon over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add whole egg and egg yolk and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: 24 hour oven roast
directions: Wrap in 3 layers of heavy-duty foil.
Cook in oven at 225° for 18 to 24 hours.
Serve with your favorite salsa.
It is best to put the wrapped roast on a cookie sheet or a pan to catch any drippings that may leak out.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley and nuts.
Cheeses mix better if at room temperature.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill overnight.
Form into a ball and roll in parsley and nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruited pork chops
directions: Cook pork over medium heat until brown.
Drain.
Place pineapple, prunes and apricots over pork.
Pour salad dressing over fruit and pork.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until pork is done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dig deep salad(make night before!)
directions: Note:
This layered salad is very versatile.
A clear big bowl (you can purchase a dish for layered salads) makes a good dish to serve in and pretty to look at too!

title: reese's candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; roll into balls.
Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate, then put on wax paper!

title: cranberry fruit bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Pour orange juice into measuring cup.
Add orange rind, melted shortening and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Combine orange juice mixture and well beaten egg.
Stir liquid mix into dry ingredients (only until dry ingredients are dampened).
Fold in chopped cranberries and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 5 x 13-inch).
Push batter to sides and corners.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: banana-apple oat muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups; dust with small amount of oat bran. Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Combine oat bran, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in small bowl.
Add to banana mixture; stir just until moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: baked chicken with apples
directions: Cook whole cabbage in boiling salted water for about 5 minutes until outer leaves are soft enough not to break when bent.
Drain and separate leaves, removing any thick stalks.
Saute onion in butter for about 5 minutes; add meat and seasonings and cook additional 10 to 15 minutes until meat is lightly browned.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Cook in frying pan until peanuts are well coated, then bake in slow oven.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, then add milk and vanilla.
Butter pan real good, then pour mixture in.
Sprinkle nutmeg.
Pour into dish or crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until set.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for a few minutes, then add jello.
Take off stove and stir it up real good, then add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir well.
You need two 1-gallon milk jugs.
Fill each jug half full of mixture.
Add water to finish filling milk jugs.
Chill.

title: danish pastry
directions: Mix flour and margarine like pie crust.
When blended, add 2 Tbsp. water and make into a ball.
Divide ball in half and spread two 3 X 13 strips onto a cookie sheet.

title: low calorie banana-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven
Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick
cooking
spray and set aside, or use tube pan. Into
a small mixing bowl sift together flour, baking powder, salt
and cinnamon.
Set
aside.
In
a
large
mixing
bowl, combine margarine and sugar.
Using electric mixer beat until creamy and light.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until thoroughly combined.
Add sifted
ingredients alternately with
bananas, beating
gently after each addition.
(Do not overbeat as this will toughen bread.)

title: hillbilly dump cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges, eggs, oil and 1 box pudding mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix 1 box pudding and pineapple when you put cake in the oven.
After cake is cool, mix Dream Whip and milk until stiff, then add other mixture.
Top cake with walnuts and cherries, if desired.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In a boiler, mix 1 1/2 cups of sugar and flour.
Put other 1/2 cup of sugar in small frying pan.
Mix egg yolks and milk and add to sugar and flour mixture.
Cook this mixture, stirring constantly, until thick.
Set aside and brown your 1/2 cup of sugar.
(Just brown; do not burn.) Add this brown sugar to first mixture with margarine and vanilla.
Stir good and pour into your crust.
Place meringue on top.

title: overnight salad
directions: Wash and chop vegetables.
Place all in a large bowl.
Top with the cheese and 2 cups of Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss well before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all.
Drop onto cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Melt in Velveeta.
Season with oregano to taste.
Place slices of rye on large tray.
Spoon on Ragu.
Then add slice of Monterey Jack and then spoon on meat mixture.
Cover and freeze.
After frozen, transfer pizzas to bags. Reheat in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak first 3 ingredients for 2 hours in ice water and 3/4 cup salt.
Mix vinegar, sugar, dry mustard and celery seed.
Cook for 3 minutes; place in jar and seal.

title: cherry delight
directions: Dissolve gel in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add pie filling until slightly thickened.
Pour into jello mold.
Blend cream cheese with pineapple and spread over jello.
Chill.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop beef.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into ball and chill slightly.
Garnish with chopped pecans, parsley and paprika.

title: 12 vegetable stew
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil over medium heat until onion is clear.
Add dill weed and stir about 1 minute. Add dissolved tomato paste.
Stir.
Add water.

title: california salad
directions: Break up lettuce.
Chop garlic and onion.
Slice mushrooms. Chop tomato.
Slice zucchini and cucumber.
Crumble bacon and cheese.
Mix all together; chill.
Use honey mustard or poppy seed dressing.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, spread in plate.
Top with chopped ripe olives, lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: pecan breakfast rolls
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pecans on the bottom. Make 24 walnut size balls of thawed dough and lay on top of pecans.
Mix melted butter, sugar, milk and pudding and spread over rolls.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Take off foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn over on foil.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: seafood salad
directions: Drain pasta and cool.
Add crab, onions, peas and tomato. Blend together mayo, sour cream, mustard, vinegar and seasoning. Blend gently the two mixtures.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar and flour. Alternate layers of apples, cranberries and sugar mixture in pastry-lined pie plate, beginning and ending with apples.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust that has slits in it.
Seal and flute.

title: tuna loaf with creamy egg sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, flake tuna.
Stir in bread crumbs, eggs, onions, lemon juice, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup sour cream and 2 tablespoons pimentos until blended.
(Reserve remaining sour cream and pimentos for sauce.) Spoon mixture evenly into loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Meanwhile, prepare Egg Sauce.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Spread half in bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetables on top and sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over vegetables.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. On foil-lined baking sheet, bake potatoes 1 hour until just tender; let cool. (Can be roasted a day ahead and refrigerated; bring to room temperature to continue.)

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Heat margarine and marshmallows in saucepan until thick and syrupy. Add vanilla. Pour over cereal. Press into a greased pan. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: In a
slow
oven melt butter, cream cheese, milk, salt, pepper and
garlic
powder
to
taste.
Stir in corn and green chilies. Put in casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: creamy zucchini quiche
directions: Spread mustard on bottom of pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add oysters and juice.
Bring almost to boiling.
Add half and half, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until oysters begin to curl.
Makes about 5 cups of stew.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes as you would for potato salad.
Cut into cubes and place in casserole dish.
Add onions if desired.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Add dry ingredients. Drain fruit well.
Add to orange mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into
1/2-inch
strips
after
pounding
in flour, salt and pepper to meat rubbed with garlic.
Brown meat in heavy pan
(like	pressure
cooker)
in
butter until quite brown. Remove meat
and
brown
onion.
Pour
mushrooms
and liquid and extra water
into
hot
pan
to
loosen the browned drippings; stir into a
brown gravy.
Add chicken soup (1 to 2 cans, depending on how much meat you have).
Stir until a nice creamy consistency, adding
more water if necessary.
Add meat and cook on low for at least 20 minutes.
Add sour cream a few minutes before serving.
Heat
well
but
do
not boil.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: shrimp and crab salad
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add shrimp, crab (or all shrimp) and mayonnaise.
Mix and serve.

title: kraut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in kraut.
Bake in 2 layer pans or oblong at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides and place layers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle layer of sausage, then layer of cheese. Repeat with bread, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs into milk until well blended. Do not overbeat.
Salt and pepper to taste and pour milk and egg mixture over other ingredients.
Press down with spatula or hand until milk covers top of ingredients. Refrigerate, uncovered, overnight. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat 1/2 cup milk into egg yolks.
Add cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Heat remaining 2 cups milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add egg mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from stove.
Stir in butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Let cool.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Clean chilies; rinse and dry.
Place Monterey Jack cheese strips in chilies and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Gradually add flour and beat until smooth.
Add salt and milk; blend thoroughly.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over chilies. Spread egg mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
May be garnished with crisp-cooked crumbled bacon or bacon bits.

title: deep dish turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mash enough of the sweet potatoes to measure 1/4 cup; reserve for Sweet Potato Biscuits. Cut remaining sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.

title: chicken in honey mustard sauce(low-fat)
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook chicken (use no fat spray) until brown on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
Pour off fat.

title: three chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Boil for 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Add chocolate bars and baking chocolate; stir until melted.
Fold in vanilla and pecans. Mix well.
Pour into greased 5x10x1 pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 5 1/2 pounds of very good fudge!

title: cream cheese chicken soup
directions: Saute the onion in butter; add broth, carrots and potatoes. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add chicken, parsley, salt and pepper. Heat. Combine flour and milk until smooth. Add to vegetable mixture. Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes, stirring until thickened. Reduce heat, add cream cheese; stir until melted. Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients except nuts.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and nuts. Add dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: anise cutouts
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Add anise; knead on flour board 5 to 6 minutes.
If dough is sticky, add a little flour.
Cookie dough shouldn't stick to hand.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and cut on floured board with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar sprinkles.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Bake until cookie turns light brown around edges.

title: beef delicious
directions: Grease skillet and add beef, onions, salt and pepper and cook until brown.
Cook macaroni and drain.

title: coconut fruit dip
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk. Set aside to thicken.
This takes only a few minutes.
Fold in thawed whipped topping.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit.

title: diabetic oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream of turnip soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes. Stir in rest of ingredients and heat.

title: reba's salad
directions: Stir lemon gelatin until dissolved in water.
Boil pineapple and add marshmallows.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Mix topping as follows; whip until stiff Dream Whip.
Add mayonnaise. Spread on top of gelatin and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese (use 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish).

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Break chicken into bite sized pieces. Mix all ingredients together and pour into one of the pie shells. Place the remaining pie shell on top of the chicken mixture. Pinch around the edge.
Bake until top crust is brown.

title: chicken stuffed peppers
directions: Combine chicken, onion, lemon juice, thyme, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup tomato sauce and mix well.
Divide filling among peppers.
Stand peppers in a casserole; pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 250° oven, basting occasionally, for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
(This dish goes lo-cal with chicken instead of beef.)

title: tangerine punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cool and add juices. Combine with ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together 2 1/4 cups of flour, the butter and confectioners sugar in a large bowl until a soft dough forms.
Remove and press dough into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated oven.
Remove from oven.
Beat the sugar, lemon juice, 1/4 cup flour, the eggs and lemon peel until well mixed.
Pour over hot crust.
Return to oven and bake an additional 20 minutes or until set.
Cool on wire rack and cut into bars.
Center will be soft.
Dust with confectioners sugar. These freeze well.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Peel banana, apple and tangerine and cut up.
Mix fruit.
Then mix yogurt and vanilla and pour over fruit.
Eat.
Fantastic.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Crumble crackers and cover bottom of casserole dish.
Cut up chicken and place on crackers.
Melt butter and spread over chicken.
Combine soups and sour cream. Spread over layers.
Crumble more crackers and cover top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grits
directions: Bring
salted
water to a boil.
Add grits.
Lower heat and stir occasionally.	When grits get to desired consistency, stir in margarine and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Heat together with the next 5 ingredients. Layer meat sauce and shells in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until bubbly at 350° (30 to 40 minutes).

title: chile relleno
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Layer cheeses and chiles in a 9-inch square pan.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add milk.
Slowly sprinkle in flour; mix well.
Pour mixture over cheese and chiles. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then cut into small pieces.
Serve while hot.

title: dream pie
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Measure 1/2 cup juice and add sugar and cornstarch.
Put in double boiler over medium heat and cook until thick.
Add cherries and pineapple and cook a few minutes until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello. Cool.
Then add nuts and bananas.
Put into three prepared graham cracker pie crusts.
Add Cool Whip or whipping cream on top of pies.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat. Add flour, salt and soda, mixing well.
Add potato chips and nuts. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: kitchen floor pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in glass or plastic gallon jar.
Pack tightly and add salt, alum, pickling spice and vinegar.
Fill jar rest of way with water.
Put lid on tightly and let stand 1 month. Remove from jar and wash off pickles.
Cut into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Put back in jar and sprinkle with sugar alternating layers, first pickles, then sugar, then pickles, etc.
Put lid on and shake well until sugar is turned into liquid.
Put in refrigerator and keep there.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Combine cake mix with eggs, oil, buttermilk, cocoa and food coloring.
Do not add ingredients listed on box mix.
Bake according to directions on cake box.

title: chicken with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all vegetables in a bowl.
Add tomato sauce diluted with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Arrange chicken in an oven roaster.
Pour sauce and vegetables over it.
Bake at 450° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered. Serve hot with rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything together at one time. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.

title: farmer's market sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except bagels, cheese and tomato.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisply-tender (4 to 5 minutes).

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onion and peppers.
Add Tony's, garlic salt and cayenne pepper to taste.

title: hamburger-potato hot dish
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Brown hamburg and onions; drain. Make layers of potatoes and hamburger; salt and pepper to taste. Mix soups together with water and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and salt.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients, except lettuce.
Toss well; refrigerate. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: marzetti
directions: Saute onion and celery and add to hamburger mixture.
Cook noodles in salted water until done; drain and add to meat mixture. Put in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be eaten before baking.
This dish freezes very well.
One small green pepper can be added with the onion and celery.
Serves 8 to 10 normal appetites.

title: punch
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients together.
Freeze concentrate, then add ginger ale when you serve.

title: jan's chinese b-b-q
directions: For
sauce:
Combine
all
ingredients	(except
meat). Simmer on top of stove and
mix
well.
Pour over meat and let stand in refrigerator 7 to 8
hours or overnight.
Ribs can be cooked in oven or on	barbecue grill until tender.
If cooking in oven, cover
with foil and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300° or until tender.

title: hushpuppies
directions: Mix and drop in hot grease until brown.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Place on cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Allow to cool and store in airtight container.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a rolling boil.
Let it boil for 1 minute, stirring now and then.
Take off stove and beat in peanut butter, vanilla and crackers.
Spread into a buttered 13 x 18-inch pan.
When it sets a little, cut into desired squares.

title: turkey tetrazzini(microwave recipe)
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and bouillon cube. Stir in water and milk.
Heat on Medium 6 minutes uncovered or until thick.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in spaghetti, turkey and mushrooms.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and heat on Medium for 6 minutes uncovered.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar in a mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, put the oleo or Crisco, cocoa and water. Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add the baking soda and vanilla.
Mix and pour into greased 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325°.

title: crisp bread and butter pickle slices
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin.
Add onions, pepper and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt, cover with cracked ice, mix thorougly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to a boil. Seal in hot sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: peanut butter 'n' chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with foil and grease well.
Cut cookie dough into 4 lengthwise pieces and place on foil-lined pan.
Press with heel of hand to evenly spread over bottom of pan to make a crust.
Smooth with a table knife.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Make brown roux and add 4 cups water.
Heat until it comes to a simmer, then add vegetables, except okra and simmer.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, chicken and seafood seasoning. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add okra and cook on low heat until okra is tender.
Add file, salt and pepper.
Serve on rice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes, melt 1/4 cup margarine, add salt, pepper, onion, chicken soup, sour cream and cheese to butter.
Stir; fold in potatoes, spread mixture in greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix corn flakes in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour over top of mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix all above and refrigerate until firm.
Serves 12.

title: marshmallow-chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except Marshmallow Creme and cook until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat, add Marshmallow Creme and blend.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, butter, lemon juice and lemon rind; mix well.
Blend in milk, cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens; cool.
Fold in sour cream, pour into pie shell.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the 6 tablespoons of sugar, beating until meringue is stiff and glossy and all sugar is dissolved.
Spread over filling.
Bake for 10 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tijuana train wreck
directions: Combine and simmer ingredients for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Line pan (approximately 9 x 12-inch) with dried beef.
Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Wrap with 2 strips bacon and place on dried beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 3 hours at 350°.

title: smoked turkey on grill
directions: You will also need a smoker, charcoal and hickory chunks.

title: nick's beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 4 to 12 hours.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Drop mixture by serving spoon on cookie sheet.
Cover with Saran Wrap and roll into thin patties.
Peel off Saran Wrap.
Dry in 150° oven for 4 to 6 hours.
Let door open.

title: eggplant pate
directions: Poke the eggplant all over with fork.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Cool and peel.
In a blender, blend the garlic, tahini and lemon peel.
Add eggplant.
Put in dish with the olive oil and cayenne pepper on top.

title: "lime punch"
directions: Mix all
together in a 1 gallon jar.
Finish filling to the top with water.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Drain and put in bean pot.
Pour boiling water over salt pork.
Scrape the rind until white, score in 1/2-inch strips and bury in beans.
Leave only rind showing.
Mix salt, mustard and molasses in a cup filled with hot water and mix well.
Pour over the beans.
Add water to cover. Bake at 250° to 350° for 6 to 8 hours.
Add more water to cover until the last hour.
Remove cover and raise pork to top to get crisp.

title: bojangle biscuits
directions: Mix well, cut out.
Spread melted margarine on top before baking.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 12 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp or sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute shrimp or sausage and green onions in oil in large heavy pot until shrimp turn pink or sausage is warmed through.
Remove shrimp or sausage and set aside.
Add garlic, rice and parsley and mix well with remaining oil in pot.
Add bay leaves, thyme, crushed peppers and stock or water.
Simmer until rice is tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Add shrimp or sausage and salt.
Serve in soup plates with paprika and fresh parsley and lemon wedge garnish.
Serves 6.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash vegetables.
Separate leaves from stems.
Slice radishes, onion and mushrooms.
Toss vegetables together.
Make tiny balls of cream cheese.
Add balls of cream cheese to vegetables.
(Not all of the cream cheese may be used.) Add Italian dressing to taste.
Toss salad.
Chill for an hour or serve immediately.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Microwave chips, peanut butter and margarine together. Stir in vanilla; mix well. Pour over cereal; mix together and pour into large plastic zip bag with confectioners sugar. Shake well to coat cereal.

title: chicken and shrimp supreme
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with mushroom soup mixture, then arrange shrimp on top, then mushrooms, green pepper, pimiento and cheese.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on Medium-high 9 to 10 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix yeast, milk, sugar and flour.
Let stand for 1/2 hour. Add eggs (beaten well), margarine, salt and flour.
Mix well. Cover with damp cloth.
Do not refrigerate.
Let set overnight. Knead dough.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out each part as for a pie.
Cut 8 wedges with a pizza cutter.
Roll into crescents. Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: cranberry oat muffin
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add orange juice, applesauce, Egg Beaters, pineapple and cranberries.
Mix until moistened.
Spray muffin pans with pam.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate after cooling.
Freezes well. Serves 24 large muffins.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, marshmallows, soda and vanilla (batter will be thin).
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch square pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice.

title: peach shake
directions: Take 4 buckets of black dirt.
Add 3 quarts of well water. Stir well with both hands.
Apply liberally to front of clothes, feet, face and kitchen floor.
Guaranteed to stick to the ribs and drive your mother up the wall.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Break bacon into small pieces. Add cheese and onion.
Just before serving, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to salad and let stand for a while until the sugar dissolves.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Bring margarine to room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix with margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients and use hand to make dough.
Make small balls and flatten with thumb on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: patty's zucchini sauce
directions: Crush tomatoes in saucepan and set aside. Chop zucchini, onion and garlic in small pieces.
Saute in a Teflon frying pan with the oil, parsley and basil for about 10 minutes.
Add to the tomatoes and heat to boiling. Add the salt, pepper, lemon pepper, wine and cheese. Simmer, uncovered, for approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburger with onions and green pepper; drain.
Mix with rice and add remaining ingredients.
Cook together until thick.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or 12-inch Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time and flavoring.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan about 15 minutes.

title: tassies (tartlets)
directions: You need 2 tins of 12 each small muffin cups about the size of English walnuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cream cheese, flour and butter into bowl and blend as for pie crust.
Then onto creamy and smooth.
Divide into 24 even sized balls.
Press carefully into bottoms and up sides of the little muffin cups.
Next mix all remaining ingredients.
Then spoon equal amount of filling into each cup.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 250° and bake 10 to 15 minutes more until golden.

title: teriyaki wing dings
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken; pour marinade over chicken and marinate overnight.
Arrange chicken on rack in foil-lined shallow baking dish.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, basting occasionally with marinade.

title: sausage skillet supper(serves 4)
directions: Cut sausage into chunks.
Combine with rice, soup, water and margarine in large skillet on medium heat.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in peas and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve or up to 2 days. Serves 3 1/2 cups.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Combine all but nuts and cherries to smooth batter.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Turn onto cake plate.
Glaze or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: italian dressing
directions: Blend olive oil with the anchovy fillets, mashing with a fork until they are well mixed with the oil.
Add lemon juice and garlic; mix thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chew bread
directions: Melt margarine and mix in with brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in self-rising flour.
Add flaked coconut, chopped nuts and vanilla flavoring.
Mix all ingredients together well and pour into 13 x 9 cake pan.
Cook on 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done, when toothpick in center comes out clean.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour the boiling water over mixture and stir.
Let cool to lukewarm temperature.
Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add to lukewarm batter.
Stir in the flour.
If dough is too sticky, add a little more flour.
Let rise.
Punch down and let rise again. Place dough into two loaf pans.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vinegar pecan pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Place in an iron skillet or griddle.
It will brown bottom of the pie.

title: banana fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients as you would pancakes.
Fry until golden brown.

title: squash patty
directions: Melt margarine in heavy boiler.
Mix flour and milk with well beaten egg.
Stir into margarine; cook slowly until thickens. Brown on side.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve chilled.
Store remaining salad in refrigerator.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Add sugar and salt; cool. Add eggs. Soak yeast in cold water 5 minutes and add to mixture. Add flour and blend well.
Set in refrigerator.
Make into rolls by pinching small bits of dough and rolling into a ball, 3 to each muffin tin for cloverleaf.
Let raise 1 to 2 hours before baking. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: italian beef by mavis
directions: Combine roast, onions, salt and water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until barely tender.
Remove roast to cool.
Slice thin.
To liquid in roaster, add the rest of seasonings, bring to a boil and add peppers.
Add sliced meat to liquid.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve warm on hard rolls; cut and place liquid from meat on each piece of roll and then top with meat. The more you heat it, the better it gets.
Our family gets together often and this recipe is great for crowds.
It's virtually work free when planned ahead of time.
A nice salad makes the meal complete.
Nice, too, for the main dish for a "pot luck".

title: killer meat loaf
directions: Mix together and shape it as a loaf of bread (oval).
Add a pinch of garlic powder, oregano and parsley flakes to the top of loaf.
Bake in oven at 425° for 45 minutes or until cooked.

title: banana punch
directions: Use bananas that are not too ripe.
Mash like potatoes but not in blender.
Pour lemon juice over the bananas.
Dilute orange juice with the 3 cans of water.
Add pineapple juice.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and 12 cups water until dissolved.
Mix all these ingredients together at this point.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine crumbs, eggs and milk.
Stir in sugar, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add ground meat.
Make a loaf and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mai tai slush
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherbet, rum and Triple Sec in blender.
Add ice; blend until slushy.
Garnish with lime slices, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: diabetic barbecued pork
directions: Combine all barbecue sauce ingredients in a 10-inch skillet. Bring to boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Add pork slices and stir to coat.
Cover and heat 5 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Serve on buns for sandwiches or as an entree.
Yield:
4 servings. Serving size:
4 ounces pork plus sauce without bun.
Exchange:
4 meat, 1 veg and 1 fat.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter over low heat in skillet; add soups and mushrooms, sour cream and turkey.
Cook noodles, drain and add to mixture. Pour all into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and cracker crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of an ungreased sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch) or jelly roll pan, pinching the edges of rolls together to seal.
Brush dough with beaten egg. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes. Cool.

title: dump cake no. 2
directions: Combine all ingredients in a big bowl and mix well.
Mixing is a little difficult at first.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and butter.
Add beans and stir several minutes.
Pour in tomatoes, salt, flour and chili powder. Cook for 45 minutes on low heat.
Serve hot and with grated cheese on the top of the bowl.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg with fork and pat into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar and chopped nuts, if desired.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except grated cheese).
Spread into oblong baking pan like lasagna pan.
Grate cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Let sit; serve with crackers or little pieces of bread.
Great for taking to a party.

title: soup-er easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix soup, milk, onion, pepper and dry mustard.
Fold in frozen hash browns.
Spread into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian hunters stew
directions: Heat oil, brown meat.
Add garlic and onions, saute well, turning often.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, flour, salt, chili powder, oregano and parsley.
Add 2 c. water and simmer covered 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Add carrots and simmer until they are tender; cook ziti, add to stew and serve with cheese on top.

title: tortilla chips
directions: Take package of flour tortillas and cut in eighths.
Put on cookie sheets in batches. Spray oil on chips and bake with oven at 350° until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Dip meat in egg, then in flour and salt and deep fry in fat at 360° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients and bring to boil.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to mixture to thicken.
Add pineapple, green peppers, onions and pork. Cook until hot, about 4 minutes.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in a very large heavy kettle.
Add water; cover and soak overnight.
Next day, add onion, green pepper, celery, ham, salt, cayenne and black pepper to the beans in their soaking water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Lower heat so that liquid ripples gently.
Cover; simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir in onion tops and parsley.
Turn heat to lowest point and cook, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Serve over beds of hot, fluffy rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy chicken piccata
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Coat chicken cutlets with flour mixture.
Melt the butter in a frying pan and brown chicken on both sides.
Stir the brown bits that form in pan and cook 1 minute.
Remove chicken from the pan and place on platter.
Add lemon juice, water and parsley to the pan and cook until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken and garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add water and let come to a boil before putting on meat.
This is especially good with steak.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put in tight container so you can invert and turn it for 3 days before using.
Stores for 3 months in refrigerator.

title: boiled peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 3 to 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and drop on waxed paper while hot.
Cool.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat flour and milk alternately.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan 3 1/2 hours at 250°.
Remove from oven.
Cool slightly and pour mixture of 1 can orange juice and 2 cups powdered sugar over cake while still in pan.
Let stand overnight before removing from pan.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt
chocolate
in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after
each
one.
Blend
in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour with
soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture,
beating after each addition until smooth. Fold in beaten
egg
whites.
Pour	into
four (9-inch) layer pans. Grease
and
flour	pans
very
well.
Bake at 350° for about
30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting mix.
Frost between layers and sides also.

title: five minute fudge cake
directions: Put oil in a 9-inch square pan and slosh around until sides and bottom are coated.
Add water, egg, sugar, flour, soda, salt, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix 2 minutes or until smooth with fork and spatula (all in the baking dish).
Sprinkle chocolate bits and nuts over top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
No frosting is necessary.
Cake will be moist and yummy.

title: spinach gourmet
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
In ungreased 1-quart casserole, mix spinach and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix together and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add celery and soups.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole and cover with as many Tater Tots as you can get on. This is quick, easy and kids love it.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Form into small balls. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Yields 4 to 5 (2-inch) cookies.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in desired thickness, set aside. Mix eggs in a small dish. Mix dry ingredients in another dish. Salt and pepper tomatoes to taste according to your liking. Dip tomato slices into egg mixture then into dry mixture.
Fry in a skillet of hot bacon drippings until golden brown. Serve hot and enjoy.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onions in water and bouillon cubes until done.
Add remaining ingredients; heat until hot and serve.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage fine.
Chop pepper, onion and cucumber together. Add to cabbage.
Add rest of ingredients to slaw.
Stir together until mixed well.
Put in covered bowl and let set overnight before using.

title: paulette's southern sweet potatoes
directions: Heat potatoes in pan.
Drain off the juice.
Combine all ingredients and mix with a mixer.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix together (in saucepan) soup, tuna, milk, mayonnaise and cheese until cheese is melted.
Combine noodles and sauce in a casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: creole fish orleans
directions: In large skillet, melt Promise; saute onion, celery and garlic 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes or until thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Roll fillets.
Arrange in sauce.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes longer or until fish is done.
Remove fish to serving platter.
Remove bay leaf from sauce; discard.
Spoon sauce around fish; sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, pour the 3 soups and rice and mix together.
Put these into a greased casserole pan with cover.
Bake with cover on for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, then take cover off and bake for 1 more hour.
The paprika is just a coloring.
You just sprinkle over entire dish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need 1 tall punch bowl.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and debone.
Cut chicken into small chunks. Melt butter.
Drain mushrooms.
Add to butter.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Add soup.
Pour sour cream and cream cheese over chicken. Mix together.
Break spaghetti in small pieces.
Cook and drain. Add to chicken.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered dish at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together the dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add chocolate pieces.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken on buttered baking dish.
Cover with mixture of onion soup mix, orange marmalade and French dressing.
Cover with foil that has been punctured.
Bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve with rice, noodles or baked potatoes. Serves 4 to 8.

title: leche flan (custard)
directions: Scald the milk in double boiler for 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks.
Add the sugar, milk and flavoring.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Place this in a large pan half-filled with water.
Steam or bake for about 1 hour or until mixture becomes firm.
Cool before removing from mold.
(If desired, line mold with the caramel syrup before pouring in mixture for steaming or baking.)
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: dixie relish
directions: Dissolve salt in 2 qts. cold water.
Pour over chopped vegetables and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Comnbine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Add vegetables and simmer about 20 minutes. Bring to a boil.
Pack boiling hot into jars leaving 1/2 inch head space.
Adjust lids.
Process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath. Makes 5-6 pints.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add beef and cook over medium heat about 20 minutes, turning often to brown evenly.
Stir in next 13 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf and garlic.
Add carrots, whole onions and potatoes; cover and simmer 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are done.
Gradually add 1/4 cup cold water to flour in a little mixing bowl, mixing well.
Pour into stew, stirring constantly until gravy thickens.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cajun christmas mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large, shallow roasting pan, combine almonds, cereal and goldfish crackers.
Melt margarine and stir in seasonings.
Pour over almond mixture and toss to coat. Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
When cool, store in airtight container.
Yields 9 cups.

title: borden sweetened condensed milk lemon pie
directions: Beat egg and add to bowl containing the condensed milk. Add lemon
peel and juice and stir until thickened.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill several hours before serving.

title: borsch(ukrainian christmas soup)
directions: Simmer the dried mushrooms in 3 cups of water for 1 hour. Strain them through a cheese cloth, but save the stock.
Wash mushrooms thoroughly and save.

title: "no bake" chocolate, peanut butter, oatmeal cookies
directions: Put stick of butter in a pan and melt.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Bring to a boil, then add oatmeal and peanut butter; stir with a spoon 1 minute.
Remove pan from heat and drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Wait until hardened and cooled.

title: potato salad
directions: Add all ingredients to potatoes.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, add 3 or 4 hard-boiled eggs and 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: sweet potato gingerbread
directions: Coat a 9 x 9-inch baking pan with spray.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Coat with spray and set aside.
Beat eggs at high speed of electric mixer 2 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add soup, tomatoes and chicken broth. Simmer 5 minutes.
In casserole, layer 1/2 chicken, 1/2 chips, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars, Crisco, vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; add to sugar mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in oatmeal and then nuts or raisins.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; chop coarsely.
Chop onion finely.
Mix broccoli, cheese, soup and onion together.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread on top of mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hornet cake
directions: Combine the pudding mix with the 2 cups milk.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour this over the cake mix and cream together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until edges are brown.
Remove and let cool.

title: spice meringue bars
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine brown sugar and spices and add to eggs gradually, beating well to blend.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Spread over first mixture.

title: rhubarb strawberry dessert
directions: Place cut up rhubarb in greased 9 inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and strawberry
jello over the rhubarb.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the the jello and sugar.
Pour the water over all and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve topped
with Kool Whip.

title: peaches and cream
directions: In a bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, peach juice and vanilla. Spread over peaches and batter in pan.
Take a mixture of sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top of cake.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: gooey yellow cake
directions: Mix together and spread over top of the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip dollop on top.
Yes, you bake the cake with the frosting on it!

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and place in ice cream freezer bucket.
Finish filling with milk.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix potatoes, carrots, onion, parsley flakes and bouillon cube in about 2 cups of water.
Cover and simmer until soft.
Mix flour and milk until combined.
Add to potatoes and carrots.
Lower heat and heat until it thickens a little.
Stir in ham and cheese until these melt.

title: roast pork with spiced cherry sauce
directions: Season roast with salt, pepper and sage.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 160°.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cut onions into chunks and boil to tender.
Then melt butter and saute onions for 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Beat milk and eggs together and pour over onions, 1 1/2 cups cheese and crumble 25 Ritz crackers to mixture and salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and remaining crackers on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: shower dessert
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions; chill until partially set.
Add fruits; fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle nuts on top and chill until firm.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry cool whip cake(annette's birthday cake)
directions: Mix Jell-O with water; let set in refrigerator until 1/2 jelled.
Then add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add strawberries.
Then cut angel food cake into small pieces.
Put cake pieces into Jell-O mixture or add whole angel food ring and push into mixture.

title: granny m's sweet potato candy
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt into a dough.
Add a little extra sugar to stiffen, if needed.
Roll out the dough to 1/4-inch thickness onto a floured surface.
Spread peanut butter evenly over rolled out dough.
Start at one end and roll like a jelly roll.
Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Let set until firm.
Great for parties and receptions.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Blend strawberries and butter in blender.
Then add powdered sugar.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Serve on hot biscuits or rolls.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: copper pennies relish
directions: Combine carrots, onions and green peppers.
Stir the remaining ingredients together and pour over the vegetables.
Place in tightly covered container and store in the refrigerator.
Will keep for several weeks.
Drained, canned carrots may be used instead of fresh carrots.

title: lemon bread
directions: Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of the cubed bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange ham and cheeses over bread.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard together and pour over ham and cheese.
Add the remaining cubed bread and drizzle butter over top.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: stroganoff
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 5 to 8 hours on slow.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: fantastic fajitas
directions: Slice pork across grain into 1/8-inch strips.
Marinate pork strips in garlic, oregano, cumin, salt, orange juice, vinegar and hot pepper sauce for 10 minutes or overnight.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat with onions; mix with other ingredients.
Mix cornbread mix and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moon rocks
directions: Combine all ingredients except half of coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll into remaining coconut. Makes 96 confections.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Stir in cheese.
Add milk until moist.
Shape in a ball.
Roll out on a floured surface, then cut with a round cutter.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed until sugar is melted.
Completely cool before pouring over other ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover for 24 hours.
Put in jars.
Ready to eat. May be kept up to a year in the refrigerator.

title: eggless peanut butter cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add water and vanilla.
Add oil and peanut butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a greased loaf pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, soups, water and onions. Place in bottom of long Pyrex dish. Melt butter. Thoroughly spread over chicken. Add salt and pepper to chicken. Lay on top of rice. Bake, covered, for 30 to 50 minutes. Uncover and bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until chicken is brown and tender to taste.

title: no-bake bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereals, peanuts and M&M's; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture and toss to coat evenly. Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan.
Cool and cut into 3 x 3 inch bars.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Mix
ravioli and sour cream.
Place broccoli in lightly oiled 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour ravioli mixture over broccoli.
Garnish with
a
bit
of broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, remove water and grease.
Add taco seasoning, diced onion and diced pepper.
Add refried beans and salsa.
Allow to simmer 20 minutes.

title: marinated carrots # 1
directions: Let carrots cool completely; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: red hot salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Add gelatin and stir; then add applesauce.
Pour in any mold and chill.

title: mock bouillabaisse
directions: Wash thawed fish; drain.
Cut into 2-inch pieces; set aside. In 2 tablespoons butter, saute onion until limp.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes, salt, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, pepper and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add fish and wine.
Continue cooking, covered, about 10 minutes, or just until fish flakes easily with fork and vegetables are tender.
Add tomato and cook for about 3 minutes longer. Remove fish and vegetables to heated serving bowl.
Save broth.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed. Seal salad with mayonnaise. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise, then cheese. Top with bacon and chill for at least 12 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash (until tender). Add remaining ingredients using only half the cheese. Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat well the eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin to egg and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° in 2 loaf pans 35 to 45 minutes or 2 hours in tube pan.

title: napoleons
directions: Mix all together and press into a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Set aside without baking.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, eggs and pickles.
Moisten with mayonnaise/salad dressing.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with additional egg slices and olives.

title: oriental meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Add sweet and sour sauce; bake until sauce is bubbly hot, about 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9-inch pie pan.
In a saucepan, mix together the apple juice, tapioca and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and set aside.

title: zippy carrots
directions: In a small saucepan, brown butter over medium heat.
Add carrots and garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add the water and cover.
Cook until carrots are crisp-tender, about 6 minutes.
Add the green pepper and cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from the heat and stir in the ketchup and chili powder.
Serves 2.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken and cut into small pieces or cook beef and drain.
Boil together with remaining ingredients.
Pour soup into bowls and top with toppings.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 25 or 30 minutes.
Can cover with slivered almonds, if you like.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken with a little salt for 10 minutes.
Debone and set aside.
In a saucepan make a white sauce as follows:
Combine butter or margarine, flour, milk, salt and pepper; cook, stirring to medium thickness.
Cook 1/2 pound pasta and drain.
Mix all ingredients with mushrooms, 1/2 pound cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spread in pan.
Dot with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old world apple pie
directions: Combine ingredients and blend well. Sprinkle over baked pie. Return to oven and bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until topping is brown. YUM!

title: lisa's singing ambrosia
directions: Mix yogurt, Cool Whip, jello and vanilla.
Add pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Sprinkle coconut on top, if desired. Cover and refrigerate.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato in jacket until tender. Peel potato and mash in large bowl. Add powdered sugar 1 cup at a time until a firm dough is made. Roll between waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness. Remove top layer of paper. Put peanut butter on potato dough. Roll jelly roll style. Chill well. Slice into pinwheel candies.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Boil water; add salt and slowly add grits (while stirring). Keep stirring until thick.
Turn fire down and add stick of butter. Melt.
Add cheese in cubes and garlic salt.
Let melt; stir and then cool.
Set in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Rub roast with garlic, pepper and vinegar.
Pierce meat all over with a fork.
Place in roasting pan and arrange bacon slices across the meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add water as needed 1/4 cup at a time.
Baste occasionally.
At end of cooking time, place veggies around roast.
Bake 1 hour or until veggies are tender.
Baste meat with currant wine sauce and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: quickie fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.
Mix all other ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan (you may use Pam).
Combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Combine milk, oil and egg in small bowl until blended.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture just until moistened.
Spreading evenly, spoon batter quickly into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions, but do not add salt.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable spray; set aside.

title: flautas de pollo(rolled tortillas with chicken)
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour and salt.
Add chicken broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add parsley, lemon juice, onion, paprika, nutmeg, pepper and green chiles.
Stir in chicken.

title: mock hollandaise
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat (or in top of a double boiler over hot water); stir in flour until smooth.
Add evaporated milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth. Add egg yolks, one at a time and stir well.
Add remaining butter, then lemon juice.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
May be reheated.
If too thick, add a tablespoon water or lemon juice.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with electric mixer.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread pecans and coconut in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 German chocolate cake mix as package directs.
Pour over pecans and coconut.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally in thin strips.
Dredge in flour.
In large saute pan, add oil.
Heat to frying temperature.
Add steak strips.
Stir-fry to desired doneness.
Add minced onion and cut celery.
Add ginger, garlic powder and soy sauce to taste. Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Gradually stir into meat mixture. Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients; put into ice cream freezer container.
Put container in freezer; finish as usual according to freezer directions.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni as the directions are
on the box.
Add the tuna and peas and stir well.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: broccoli with sour cream dressing
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour dressing over hot broccoli and serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased casserole.
Save out enough crumbs and add to 1/2 cup melted butter for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain each can of vegetables.
Mix together.
Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, onion and sweet pepper.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain before serving.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Spray baking dish, larger than 9 x 13-inch.
Lay chicken breasts in pan.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Spread just dry bread from stuffing on cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing seasoning on bread cubes.
Melt oleo and mix with chicken broth.
Pour slowly all over bread stuffing, try to wet all the bread.
Bake 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix margarine and cookie crumbs.
Press cookies on bottom and sides of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan or glass dish.
Save some cookie mixture to sprinkle on top.
Spoon softened ice cream onto cookie crust.
Sprinkle remainder cookie crumbs on top.
