Put "cake" into freezer to firm up.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crab and clam dip
directions: Melt Old English cheese and cream cheese in a double boiler. Add onion, garlic salt, lots of pepper, crab and clams.
If needed, add clam juice to thin.
Keep in a fondue pot to keep warm.
Excellent with English muffins, crackers and when using pieces of bread for dipping.

title: meaty spanish rice pie
directions: Combine corn flakes, milk, onion, salt and ground beef in a large bowl, mixing well.
Press over bottom and side of a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine tomato sauce, rice, green pepper and chili powder, mixing well.
Spoon over ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 3 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Put in butter. Add eggs, cream and vanilla.
Chill dough.
Preheat oven to 400°. On a well floured surface, roll dough, one part at a time, 1/4-inch thick.
With floured cookie cutter, cut out cookies. Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack. Makes 12 dozen.

title: 24 hour cabbage slaw
directions: Heat the following ingredients in saucepan to boiling point and pour over cabbage and onion.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: spiced cider
directions: Add sugar to cider or apple juice. Add cinnamon and cloves which have been tied in a cheesecloth bag. Simmer 15 minutes. Remove spices and serve hot.

title: south dakota hot dish
directions: Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Brown hamburg and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made up and refrigerated.
Add milk, if necessary.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add pepper, garlic, sugar and tomato sauce; cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Mix cream cheese, onion and sour cream.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and flatten into balls of dough.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, until brown.
Do not add flour or grease cookie sheet.

title: al's ham and beans
directions: Cut cooked ham in bite-sized pieces.
Chop onion; dice celery. In a large pot cook onion in olive oil until tender.
Add ham, corn, kidney and shell beans, celery, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
and
put in crock-pot, which has been lightly greased.
Top with some cheese and cook on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Saute onions, garlic, pepper and ground beef.
Cook and stir often, mashing meat until it crumbles and browns.
Add tomatoes, ketchup, tomato sauce and all spices and seasonings.
Cook on medium slow in deep saucepan.
Add mushrooms when three-fourths done.
Add cheeses when done.
Simmer for about 10 minutes, stirring often.
(Total cooking time:
1 1/4 hours, uncovered.)

title: surprise cornbread ole
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cornbread mix and cheese.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently; keep mixture hot.
Prepare cornbread mix.
Pour meat mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Spoon cornbread on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown.
Top each serving with grated cheese, if desired.

title: soft chicken taco
directions: Place chicken in a shallow dish.
Combine the lemon and pepper in a separate small bowl and pour it over the chicken.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.
Wrap the tortillas in aluminum foil and bake at 325° until thoroughly heated (10 to 15 minutes).

title: taco party wings
directions: Combine all ingredients but chicken in a bag.
Shake wings until coated.
Place on greased pan in a single layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn over and bake 10 minutes more or until tender.

title: mud cake(great recipe for a kid's birthday)
directions: Crush the cookies in a blender or food processor.
Beat the cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Beat instant pudding and milk together.
Fold the topping with the pudding.
Fold the cream cheese mixture with the pudding.
Layer the cookies, cream cheese mixture, cookies, etc. and finish with the cookies.
Put in freezer a day before.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine in large bowl.
Mix together flour and sugar; add to margarine.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and coconut.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until filling is set and golden brown.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Marinate roast overnight in Italian dressing.
Combine all ingredients and cook in a slow-type cooker until done.
Use gravy for rice or potatoes.
Put in a little cornstarch if you want thicker gravy.
Let the roast soak in Italian salad dressing overnight.
You can also put carrots and potatoes in with roast.

title: rotel cheese dip recipe
directions: To
one
can
Ro-Tel
tomatoes and green chilies, add 1 pound of cheese which has been melted in a double boiler.
Mix together.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Put both ingredients in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all and chill.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mile hi strawberry pie
directions: In a 9	x
13-inch pan, stir in melted butter and brown sugar. Add
flour and nuts.
Pack evenly over bottom and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
In large bowl, beat egg whites to	a
soft
peak.	Gradually
add sugar, berries, lemon juice and
vanilla.
Beat at high speed until triple in volume and stiff
peaks
form.
Fold
in
cream.
Spread over cooled crust. Freeze.

title: garlic salmon
directions: Rinse fillet or steak in water and drain.
Coat fillet or steak with a mixture of olive oil and garlic.
Broil; cook 10 minutes per 1 inch thickness until flesh flakes easily with fork.

title: caramel pie
directions: Unwrap candy.
Melt caramels in water in the microwave; cool. Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into crust; chill.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon together and put into a plastic bag or bowl.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Put biscuit pieces into bag or bowl with the sugar mixture and shake or stir well.
Grease large Bundt pan well.
Drop in biscuit quarters.
If desired, sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan then place some biscuits, then nuts and continue until all biscuits have been used.

title: whole wheat angels(biscuits)
directions: In small bowl, pour water.
Add yeast; sprinkle about 1 teaspoon sugar over all.
Let set until bubbles good and all yeast is dissolved.
In meantime, mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in Crisco.
Add small amount of buttermilk, then yeast mixture. Stir.
Add remainder of buttermilk, little at a time, until batter "feels" right.
May need to add little wheat flour also.
Let batter set a few minutes, then roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter or glass (depends on what size you want biscuits to be).
Place on cookie sheet a little apart if you want crusty biscuits.
Place in Pam sprayed cake pan, letting biscuits touch, if you want puffy, high biscuits.
Bake at 425° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
May have to turn oven a little higher to brown to your liking.
Butter and enjoy!

title: chicken dumpling soup
directions: Stir with fork, will look lumpy and be pasty, not dry.
Drop by teaspoons full into boiling broth.
Cook till they all float for 5 minutes.
Take bones and skin off chicken, cut up and put back in soup.
Heat through.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies(great for christmas cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter together slowly, adding sugar gradually.
Cream until very light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Stir in sifted cake flour, baking powder and salt.

title: pumpkin crisp cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan and line with wax paper. Mix first 7 ingredients and pour over wax paper. Spread dry cake mix over mixture. Sprinkle with nuts; pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. When completely cold, turn out and add topping.

title: mini ham loaf
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
On round stone, place 1 package crescent rolls and spread around like a crust.
Put mixture on rolled out crust and spread around.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat until well blended.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 225° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Place oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat until combined.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; add to oil mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut or raisins.
Spread batter in lightly greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: no-drip chocolate dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt chopped chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly. Stir in the sweetened condensed milk and corn syrup until combined. Gradually stir in the 1/2 cup milk until combined. Stir in vanilla and cinnamon. Serve warm, stirring in additional milk as necessary, until of dipping consistency. Serve with cookies. Makes 2 cups.

title: apple dumpling hand-me-down
directions: Put some apple in each biscuit.
Pinch together and put in greased baking dish.
Next, pour sauce over the dumplings.

title: party buns
directions: Combine cheese and lunch meat; add remaining ingredients. Stuff finger rolls, putting cut side up in pan.
Cover with foil; bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Makes 48 small rolls.

title: 7-up brisket
directions: Combine 7-Up, catsup, soup mix and wine in a large, heavy Dutch oven.
Add brisket; turn several times to coat well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 2 hours.
Baste frequently with 7-Up mixture.
Remove brisket from pan.
Slice across the grain into very thin slices.
Return meat to pan and reheat over low heat.
Transfer brisket to serving platter; serve with sauce.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: peach gelatin jam
directions: To ground peaches, add pineapple, pectin and sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: holly taters
directions: Mix all spices with flour and roll potatoes in mixture.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; place potatoes in margarine. Bake at 400 ° until browned and done.
Turn over once during baking.

title: dressed chicken breasts with angel hair pasta
directions: Mix salad dressing and mustard.
Saute chicken in butter until browned.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Pour wine into skillet. Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Whisk in salad dressing. Blend well.
Serve chicken with sauce over pasta.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: aunt lora's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add dry and wet ingredients alternately.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased pan (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 12-inch).

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put a well-greased 2-quart baking dish in the oven to heat.
In a medium saucepan, boil the milk. Gradually stir in the corn meal; the mixture should be stiff.
Add the salt and butter.
Turn off the heat and add the baking powder. Beat the egg yolks and add them to the batter.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour the batter into the hot, greased baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until spoon bread is firm in the middle and brown on top.

title: mexican rice dish
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in rice and coat with butter.
Add stock, wine and chile peppers.
Bring to a boil and transfer to ovenproof casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from oven.
Turn oven up to 400°.
Transfer rice to bowl and add other ingredients. Spoon into liberally buttered baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.

title: company macaroni salad
directions: Add vegetables, cheese and pickles to macaroni.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and salt and mix thoroughly with macaroni mix and chill.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in casserole (3-quart) dish.
Melt margarine.
Add crushed crackers; coat well.
Sprinkle crackers over vegetables.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cold tomato sauce with fusilli pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor and process until smooth.
Salt to taste.
Cool cooked pasta under cold running water and toss with sauce.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine.
Add sugar and mix well. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut, if desired.

title: dad's baked beans
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except
bacon in 1 1/2 quart casserole.	Place bacon over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and brown.	Yield:	6 servings.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: In large kettle, add all ingredients, except rice.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Serve with tossed salad, rolls, crackers and butter.
Keeps for several days in refrigerator.

title: camp stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain fat. Season with salt and pepper as desired. Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Put all ingredients in crock pot. Stew will be thick - add water as desired. Cook on low for 8 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine yeast, eggs, 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup warm water, shortening, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth at medium speed, scraping sides for 2 minutes.
Stir in rest of flour with wooden spoon until makes soft dough.
Cover. Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour in a warm place.
Punch down. Refrigerate overnight.
(Flavor is better if let set 2 to 3 nights.)
About 4 hours before baking, roll out.
First divide dough in half.
Roll each 1/2 into 1/2-inch thick rectangle. Spread generously with melted butter.
Roll up jelly roll style. Cut in 12 pieces.
Put in greased muffin cups.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place 3 to 5 hours.
Bake.

title: eclair cake(easy do-ahead dessert)
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip or heavy cream.
Pour half of mixture over crackers, cover with a layer of crackers, filling mixture and finish with a layer of crackers.
Prepare frosting.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients well, then pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon. Remove bacon and set aside.
Save bacon grease.
Put some aside to fry eggs.
Add to bacon grease 1/2 chopped onions, 1/2 cup water and soy sauce.
Cook until onions are tender.
Cook rice.
Scramble eggs in another pan (with some of the bacon grease).
When cooked, break up the eggs as fine as you like them. Put rice in pan and stir together with water, onions and soy sauce.
If too much liquid remains, keep cooking until you get however dry/moist you like.
Crumble bacon and eggs into pan and you're done.

title: german potato soup
directions: Note:
Can use a frozen package of California Blend instead of 1 package broccoli, 1 package of cauliflower and 5 cups of carrots.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar and beat until consistency of whipped cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sifted flour and baking powder, then add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and milk; add lemon and vanilla flavorings; beat until combined.
Stir in coconut.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before inverting cake onto wire rack or cake plate.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes until no longer translucent in center.
Remove shrimp to a bowl with slotted spoon.
Add potatoes to saucepan; simmer 4 to 6 minutes until tender.
Add milk.
Bring just to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove form heat.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Let stand 2 minutes until cheese melts.
Stir in shrimp and serve.

title: herbed pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans. Stir until blended. Add pecans; toss until coated. Place in single layer in roasting pan. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes, stirring often. Drain well. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: pancit bihon guisado(sauteed rice sticks)
directions: Cook chicken and pork with water in a pot and bring to a boil. Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain, but save broth.
Remove meat from chicken and cut into small pieces.
Cut pork about the same size as chicken meat.
Saute garlic and onions in hot oil in a large skillet.
Add meats and fish sauce.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Add about 2 cups of broth and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce beef and add bihon, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until bihon is tender. Add more broth if mixture becomes too dry before noodles are done. Serve hot, garnished with quartered eggs, green onions and lemon wedges.
Serve patis with lemon juice in a small bowl for extra seasoning.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough onto a greased cookie sheet.
Pinch perforations between individual rolls to seal dough.
Combine cream cheese, egg, flour, first sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Spread filling over dough.
Combine second sugar, pecans and cinnamon and sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Fold dough around filling.
Sprinkle with additional nuts.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until browned.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll in pecans.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat, add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onions (thin sliced), and celery (cut small).
Add molasses.
Cover well with water and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: cider treat
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients except lemon slices. Cover; cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot with lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend butter and sugar. Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and egg yolks.
Add salt, spices, sweet potatoes and hot milk.
Put into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn temperature to 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: kansas corn scallop
directions: Drain whole kernel corn, reserving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Beat eggs slightly in a large bowl.
Stir in corn and 1/4 cup of liquid. Add cream style corn, evaporated milk, melted butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in saltines and diced cheese.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: almost yeast rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in baking dish.
Roll out and cut in desired shape.
Place rolls in pan.
Turn to coat top and bottom.
Bake at 400° until done, about 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken in salted water until done; remove from bones.
Place in greased casserole dish.
In saucepan, mix the chicken broth and soup.
Bring to boil and pour over chicken.
In a bowl, mix the flour, buttermilk, margarine and pepper to form batter; spoon batter over broth.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Oven temperatures vary; it may take a little longer to become golden brown.)

title: avocado dip
directions: Halve, pit and peel avocado.
Mash well.
Stir in lemon juice, onion and garlic powder.
Add this to the cream cheese and blend well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: peach jam(microwave)
directions: Mix pureed peaches with sugar.
Microwave for 6 minutes on High, uncovered, in 6 cup dish.
Store, covered, in refrigerator about 2 months.
Only make 1 batch at a time.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: megan's favorite pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In a large bowl, combine sliced olives, salami, onion, cheese, parsley and Italian dressing.
Add pasta and toss well. Chill overnight.
Great for picnics.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add chips and pecans and mix well.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Place in preheated 350° oven and turn oven off.
Leave all day or night or at least 4 hours.
Do not open oven until at least 4 hours.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: golden china fried rice
directions: Add 1 tablespoon oil to well heated skillet.
Add rice and cook until thoroughly heated.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste with soy sauce, salt and pepper.
If rice starts to burn or is too dry, may add a few drops of water.

title: wacky wild snow cones
directions: Put the sugar sweetened soft drink mix and water in a pitcher or a bowl.
Stir the mixture until the drink mix is dissolved. Ask Mom to help crush some ice and place in bowls or cups.
Pour the mixture over the crushed ice.
Share with a friend.
Dig in!

title: cheese pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet about 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Fold in pineapple, Cool Whip, peanuts and apples.
Refrigerate.

title: dandy candy bars
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in pan and cook over heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and add Special K cereal.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Frost bars.
Cool and cut.

title: super moist pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 minute at slow speed, 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tangy vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with vegetables.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes (less if using glass pans).

title: kitteney's chocolate pudding cake
directions: A cake that makes its own pudding sauce as it bakes!

title: patties beef stew
directions: Boil meat in water with garlic salt for two hours.
Drain. Wash out pan.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for four hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound both sides of steak with a mallet or edge of saucer.
Brown in oil in a large skillet. Pour off excess oil.
Add onions, garlic, tomato sauce and water. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Break cauliflower into bite size flowers.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
In 3-quart bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower and peas.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread over top evenly to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Follow with Parmesan cheese.
Top with bacon.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: *Can use fresh strawberries.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients in equal parts.
Serve cold.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal and flour in mixing bowl.
Put eggs and onion in blender.
Blend and add to dry ingredients along with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil until golden.

title: sheepherder's breakfast
directions: Cook bacon and onions until bacon is crisp.
Drain all but 1/2 cup of drippings.
Add hash browns and mix well. Cook over medium heat 10 minutes.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Puree strawberries in a blender. Blend cornstarch and sugar in a medium saucepan. Stir real good to mix. Add the pureed strawberries. Stir to mix well. Bring the mixture to a boil, then simmer for 2 minutes, stirring often. Mixture should be cooled to room temperature. Place butter in mixer bowl and whip the butter. Add the strawberry mixture slowly, beating constantly, until butter and pureed mixture are blended well. Refrigerate.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and Tang in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in rest of ingredients and pour into a lightly greased 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion in 3-quart saucepan until sausage is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, beans, broth, water, zucchini and basil; break up tomatoes with a fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until zucchini is tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: bacahlau
directions: Boil the potatoes and 3 pieces of Bacahlau together.
Separate potatoes and Bacahlau.
Cut Bacahlau in small pieces.
Then mash potatoes.
Cut onions and fresh parsley into small pieces.
Mix potatoes, Bacahlau and onion/parsley mixture.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add to Bacahlau mixture.
Make into oblong shapes and fry.

title: easy grasshopper pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Gradually increase beating speed to high (3 to 6 minutes) until soft peaks form.
Spoon into prepared crust and freeze until firm or overnight.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: oyster soup
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add oysters and cook until edges curl. Remove oysters and broth to blender and process on medium for 2 to 3 seconds (until oysters are chopped).
Return to pan and add milk and seasonings. Cook over medium-low heat until hot.

title: party pineapple punch(diabetic)
directions: Cut bananas into chunks and place in blender.
Add 1 cup of pineapple juice and orange juice concentrate.
Blend until smooth. Transfer to large bowl.
Add the remaining 2 cups of the pineapple juice and the cold water, lemon juice and Equal.
Stir to completely mix.
Pour into containers and freeze to a slush. Put into a punch bowl, pour the lemon-lime soda down the sides of the bowl.
Stir gently to mix.
Serve in small punch cups.
Yields 24 servings.

title: yummy sweet rolls
directions: Separate rolls in triangles.
Roll a marshmallow in butter, then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Roll in a triangle of dough, sealing edges tightly.
Dip bottom in butter.
Put in muffin tin. Continue with the rest of the rolls.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
If desired, frost with powdered sugar icing.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cut up medium pumpkin into small pieces and cook in a large pot with brown sugar and water until soft.
Scrape pumpkin from shell and puree in blender.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend together and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.

In medium bowl, stir together flour, sugar and cream until the dough forms a ball. Turn the dough out onto a dusted surface. Fold the dough in 1/2 and knead 5 to 7 times, adding just enough flour to keep the dough from sticking to your hands. Gently roll out dough in 1/2-inch thickness.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Add vanilla, then flour (sift with dry ingredients).
Roll into balls size of walnut and press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush taco chips in bowl.

Place layer of crushed chips in bottom of greased 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle layer of ground beef with taco seasoning on top of chips. Pour salsa and tomato mixture with green chilies over beef layer. Pour layer of refried beans.
Repeat layers until all ingredients have been used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes, until hot.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: haystacks
directions: In a heavy-duty pan, melt butterscotch morsels.
Take off heat then add noodles and cashews.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop on wax paper and put in refrigerator for five minutes.

title: deluxe waffles
directions: Whip the cream in a bowl.
Sift dry ingredients into the cream. Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Bake in hot waffle iron. When steam no longer appears, waffle is done.
Do not raise lid during baking.

title: eva  adams chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and beat. Add flour. Alternately add chocolate and salt to mixture. Place in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift salt, flour, soda and cinnamon together.
Make well in dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar, nuts, coconut and mangoes; mix well.
Put into 2 well-greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cookies(no bake)
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Form into strawberry shapes and roll in remaining Jell-O (1/2 package).
Make leaves of powdered sugar frosting, tinted green. Using fine ground coconut makes a nicer looking strawberry.

title: angel delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and juice from pineapple.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Place in refrigerator; chill for 20 minutes.
Add coconut, pecans and pineapple.
Beat whipping cream; fold into mixture.
Pour into oblong dish and chill.

title: fried apples
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into 1-inch wedges.
Place in baking dish; stir sugar with salt.
Dip apple wedges in mixture, turning to coat all sides.
In large skillet over medium-low heat, melt margarine.
Add apples and cook partially covered 15 minutes or until fork-tender, carefully turning apples with pancake turner. Remove when tender.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together melted butter, eggs and sugar
until well blended.
Add pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake in greased baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins(16 muffins)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine safflower oil, brown sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, egg, oat bran, oatmeal and wheat germ; mix lightly with a wooden spoon to moisten.
Stir in blueberries.
Fill paper-lined muffin tins 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out dry.
Remove muffins from tins and cool on wire racks.

title: asparagus cheese strata
directions: In a saucepan cover asparagus with water, cover and cook until tender but still firm.
Drain and set aside.
Lightly brush butter over one side of bread slices.
Place 1/2 of bread, buttered side up, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Layer with asparagus and ham.
Cover with remaining bread, buttered side up.
In a bowl, lightly beat eggs; add milk, onion, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Melt butter with oil.
Add onions and garlic; cook until soft. Add all other ingredients except cilantro, cheese and avocado. Simmer until ready to serve.
Place cilantro, cheese and avocado in bowl.
Cover with soup.
Top with pieces of tortilla strips.
Can add more cheese to top.

title: salad in pink
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Reserve all juice.
Add juice to gelatin in a saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend sour cream into gelatin mixture. Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Unmold or cut in squares.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Add mayonnaise. Mix in a large bowl, then add broth, salt, eggs, milk and chicken. Stir together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to cook, add soup.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese to top the last 10 minutes.

title: michael's banana creme pie
directions: Put slices of bananas in bottom of crust.
Make pudding according to package.
Pour over bananas.
Top with more banana slices.
Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sour cream together.
Fold the shrimp and onions into the cream cheese mixture.
Shape and keep refrigerated.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in pie plate or Corning Ware. Sprinkle sugar over fruit evenly. Pour water over sugar/apples or other fruit. Sprinkle cinnamon to taste when using apples. Pour dry cake mix over fruit mixture. Spread over fruit. Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake mix
directions: Bake cake mix in 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan, using egg yolks, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Blend pudding mix with milk. Beat in cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread mixture on cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter,
sugar and egg;
add milk; add dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Sprinkle a bit of sugar on top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: mexican 7-layer dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, taco mix, mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: skillet steak
directions: Trim any fat from steak & cut steak into 1 inch cubes.
Coat large non-stick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium - high heat until hot.
Add steak and cook until browned.
Remove from skillet.
Set aside.
Rinse skillet under hot water & dry. Coat again with cooking spray.
Add onion, bell pepper, & garlic to skillet & saute for 3 minutes or until tender.
Return steak to skillet.
Add tomatoes & next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Cover meat mixture, reduce heat & simmer about 30 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve over salad greens.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 of butter and pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Break up hash browns in pan and salt and pepper.

title: popcorn treat
directions: Mix together popped corn, Rice Chex and Cheerios and put aside in a bowl.
In a saucepan, put brown sugar, Karo syrup and margarine; heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and add salt and vanilla; stir.
Pour over dry mix; stir and mix well. Pour onto cookie sheet and spread out.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
After 30 minutes transfer mixture immediately onto waxed paper on another tray. Spread flat. Store in plastic bags when cool. Excellent TV snack.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until soft.
Mash.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in greased casserole.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend milk, egg and oil; gradually add to dry ingredients.
Add apples. Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep, hot fat.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Saute in oleo the mushrooms and onions. Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, eggs, soup, milk and seasonings. Grease a 2-quart casserole dish and add bread cubes on sides and bottom.
Alternate mushrooms and onions with soup mixture and cheese.
Make the day before.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, top with cheese and let it melt.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put boiling water over mix and let stand for 15 minutes to soften fruit.
Add baking powder, vanilla, eggs and flour.
Bakes well in 3 greased tennis ball cans, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Run knife around edges and remove while still quite hot.
Can also bake in greased bread pans or muffin tins.

title: chocolate chip snowballs
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Form into small balls in shredded coconut.
Refrigerate if too soft to handle.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast halves and cool. Cut into bite size chunks.
Thaw broccoli.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with broccoli.
Mix soups, mayonnaise and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour over broccoli. Top with remaining cheese.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Place on top of casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: krunchy cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, oil, margarine, egg, vanilla and milk. Add flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar which has been sifted. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except prepared dressing and chicken.
Arrange chicken in the bottom of greased casserole dish. Pour mixed ingredients over chicken.
Spoon dressing on top. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until top of dressing is lightly browned and dish bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the margarine, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in pecans and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, then coat with flour. In medium skillet, heat butter until bubbly.
Add chicken and brown lightly on both sides.
Remove chicken.
Stir in 1/3 cup water, the mustard and honey.
Return chicken to skillet, spooning sauce over each piece.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes, just until chicken is done.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix, 1/2 melted oleo, eggs, 1/2 cup grated cheese, onion, frozen broccoli and cottage cheese.
Put in well-greased pan.
Drizzle remaining melted oleo on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes (uncovered).
Sprinkle remaining grated cheese on top (approximately 1/2 cup).
Bake for another 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs and cheese, and put in casserole dish.
Mix crackers and cheese.
Put 2/3 cup on top of broccoli mixture and fold in.
Sprinkle remainder on top and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: creamed brussels sprouts
directions: Boil sprouts and celery in salt water, drain and save liquid. Measure liquid and add milk to make 1 3/4 cups.
Blend butter and flour and mix with liquid.
Cook and stir until thick, add nutmeg. Combine vegetables and sauce.
Top with cheese and brown.
Serve at once.

title: easy taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground meat and onions until brown. Drain any fat.
Pour tomato sauce, taco seasoning and corn mix; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and drain fat. Add all remaining ingredients and mix together. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix corn bread and squash; add milk and all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apples and cream pie
directions: In a bowl, mix apples, 3/4 cup sugar, flour and cinnamon. Arrange apple slices in circles in the pie shell.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, cream, vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar until well blended.
Pour mixture evenly over top of apples.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 40 minutes, covered with a piece of aluminum foil.
Remove foil and continue baking another 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve slightly warm.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, Karo, vanilla, salt and nuts. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Separate triangles and place chicken on longer end.
Place cheese and pepper on top of chicken.
Seal ends and roll up crescents.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk together; pour over rolls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: kool-aid popcorn balls(child-approved)
directions: Place popcorn in large buttered bowl.
In saucepan, bring syrup, sugar and Kool-Aid mix to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over popcorn, mixing quickly.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: open casserole broccoli
directions: Saute the celery and onions, then add to chopped broccoli, Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken mixture.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain well.
Stir together cheese, butter, eggs and flour.
Mix in broccoli.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight or roll half the dough out on a floured surface.
Cut into shapes.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or leave plain to frost.
Food coloring can be added to dough for a colored cookie.
Bake at 375° about 7 to 9 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: breakfast buns
directions: Stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter.
Combine eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moist.
Add raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased baking sheet.
Combine cinnamon and remaining sugar. Sprinkle over buns.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: * skillet dinner *
directions: In large skillet, lay bacon strips.
Top with raw meatballs and dash of salt and pepper.
Top with onion, carrots and potatoes.
Cook on top of stove on high heat for 10 minutes. Lower heat to simmer; add water and cook for 30 minutes.
Color and flavor can be enhanced by adding a package of gravy mix.

title: easy chicken and gravy
directions: Put butter in bottom of baking dish.
Flour, salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Cover chicken with water.
Put in oven.
Set on broil for 45 minutes or until done.
Turn a few times to brown on both sides.

title: creamy party dip
directions: In small bowl, blend the soup mix with the sour cream.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crisp, fresh vegetables or chips. Makes about 2 cups.

title: taffy recipe
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, butter and vinegar.
Cook constantly, stirring slowly until mixture boils.
Boil slowly, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 260° or candy hard ball stage. Remove from heat and pour into greased pan or platter.
When cool enough to handle, butter hands and pull until light golden color. Cut in 2-inch strips and let harden.
Wrap individually in wax paper and refrigerate.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Wash, scald, skin, core and chop tomatoes.
Clean peppers (remove seeds) and onion.
Chop fine.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until sauce is as thick as you want it.
Pour into hot jars. Process pints 30 minutes and quarts 45 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice. Set aside. Cream butter and sugar; add honey and eggs, beat until light and fluffy. Combine fruit and nuts in a small bowl. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the flour mixture over the fruits and nuts. Add remaining flour mixture to creamed sugar and butter, alternately with milk. Stir in fruits and nuts and spoon into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 90 minutes or until cake springs back to the touch. Cool in the pan on a wire rack for 15 - 20 minutes; trace edges with a knife to loosen from pan and turn onto rack to cool completely. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: shar's buttermilk roll dough
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water.
In a large pot, combine buttermilk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Bring to boil, turn down and let shortening melt.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Beat in yeast and eggs.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough.
Mix well with hands. Knead for 10 minutes on lightly floured surface.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with towel and let rise to double, 2 1/2 hours. Punch down.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise until double on greased and floured sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes (loaves bake at 350° for 45 minutes).

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients in order listed, in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake for 60 minutes.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cooled. Serve with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.

title: beer bread
directions: Sift together; put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mustard-dill chicken(6 servings)
directions: Heat a large skillet; add olive oil.
Dredge chicken in flour; season and brown in hot oil about one minute per side.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion a few minutes before adding all remaining ingredients, except garnish.
Blend ingredients; bring to a boil and reduce to a simmer.
Return chicken to sauce.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until sauce is thickened and chicken is still slightly soft to touch.
If a thicker sauce is desired, remove chicken to platter; bring sauce to a boil and reduce until desired thickness is reached.
Garnish with additional fresh dill.
Quick, easy, lo-cal and low-fat entree from Barbara Hill.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice margarine in bottom of pan.
Place pork chops on margarine.
Slice onion over pork chops.
Sprinkle on brown sugar; pour on catsup.
Cover with foil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven at 350°.

title: fun ice cream
directions: To get started, each child will need the bottom half of a half gallon milk carton, a small metal juice can, a metal spoon, ice and rock salt.

title: punch
directions: Mix punch and juice.
Add 7-Up slowly, stirring.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Partially defrost hash browns.
Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, cheese, onions, sour cream, soup and spices.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top of potatoes; pour the 1/4 cup margarine over cornflakes.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Place can of tomato soup in bottom of pressure cooker with 2 cans water (can add more tomatoes, if needed).
Mix all other ingredients together and make small meat balls, rice and all.
Cook approximately 10 to 15 minutes in pressure cooker with steam on high.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a roaster.
Bake at 500° for 30 minutes, then at 250° for 3 to 5 hours.
Can be doubled or frozen.

title: martha's cottage potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon (with liquid), corn meal, flour and eggs.
Drop by spoonful in hot oil.
Cook until brown; drain.

title: home donuts
directions: Take biscuits out of can.
Flatten out, cut hole in center. Fry donut and holes; roll in powdered sugar.

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into slices.
Combine sugars, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place half of the apples in crust and sprinkle with sugars.
Top with remaining apples.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lattice top and brush dough with beaten egg.

title: karen's goo
directions: Mix cottage cheese, dry Jell-O and pistachio pudding mix. Add all other ingredients and chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers in a bowl.
Top with about 1/3 of the pudding mix.
Repeat layers twice and end with pudding mix on top.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
With pastry blender, combine flour, salt, baking powder and margarine.
Add yeast/water mixture and buttermilk and mix completely.
You can refrigerate the dough at this point and use as needed.
Take out desired amount and pat out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes until brown as desired.
(Will make about 4 dozen rolls.)

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt another 1/4 stick of margarine or butter and toss with 1 cup crushed corn flakes. Drizzle over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix white cake mix and jello.
Add Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remainder of ingredients and pour into greased and floured cake tins.
Bake 3 layers at 350° until done.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and cook 1 hour at 375°.
Serve over noodles.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Heat and melt sugar, milk and butter.
Add the coconut.
Spread with a fork on the cake.
Put in broiler to brown.

title: cheesy cajun shrimp spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil until wilted.
Add garlic, butter, tomatoes and sauce.
Cook 30 minutes. Add shrimp and cook 8 minutes. Add cheese and onion tops. Blend well.
Remove from heat.
Have cooked spaghetti well drained and mix with sauce.

title: microwave fries
directions: Place a sheet of Reynolds Wrap on a microwave-safe plate; set aside.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients except potato and cheese. Cut potato into 4 or 5 thin wedges.
Roll potato wedges in spice mixture until evenly coated.
Arrange wedges on prepared plate. Sprinkle wedges evenly with cheese.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly in order as given.
Form into small balls on cookie sheet (do not flatten).
Do not crowd cookie balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix all except coconut; then add coconut.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Decrease temperature to 350°.
Bake until set and top is golden brown (about 25 minutes more), 35 minutes in all.
Do not overcook.

title: mile high pie
directions: Put egg whites, sugar, lemon juice, salt and strawberries in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed in mixer for 15 minutes. Fold in dessert topping.
Pour into pie shells and freeze.
Makes 2 pies.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine
flour
and
sugar in bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke
to boiling.
Stir in flour mixture; add buttermilk, eggs, soda
and marshmallows.
Beat by hand.
NO mixer.
This will be a thin batter with marshmallows floating on top.
Bake in large
pan or
layers,
if desired, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones. Combine chicken and all ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar and margarine in thick saucepan 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put marshmallow cream and peanut butter chips in large bowl.
Pour cooked ingredients in marshmallow cream and peanut butter chips.
Stir until all ingredients are melted. Pour in wax paper lined pan and let cool overnight.
Cut in squares and turn out.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the batter.
Add the rest of the batter over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold into sour cream. Chill overnight.

title: coconut pie
directions: Place pie shell in oven until golden brown.
Melt butter, then mix it with milk, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Cook until thick, then pour into pie shell.
Mix egg whites with 1/8 cup sugar until thick and put on pie.
Then stick in oven and brown.

title: potato wedge
directions: Place potato wedges, cut sides down, on rack in broiler pan. Brush with oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Broil with tops about 3 inches from heat until brown, about 5 minutes.
Turn; brush with oil and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Broil until tender, about 5 minutes.
Spoon sour cream onto center of large serving platter; sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange potato wedges around sour cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Then add creamed corn, beaten eggs, the buttermilk and then chopped ingredients.
Stir all together.
Fold in cheese.
Bake in a greased and floured sheet pan or in muffin tins at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill.
The longer it sits, the better it is.
Great with raw vegetables.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in oil for a few minutes; do not brown.
Add liquid to mushroom soup and stir smooth.
Add this with the remaining ingredients to sauteed mixture.
Combine.
Bake casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mixture will thicken as it stands.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place pineapple and oranges in colander; let drain (about 1 hour).
Sprinkle gelatin over cottage cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add drained fruit and mix well.
Add whipped topping.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: gingerbread sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add cold water, a little at a time.
Add margarine.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam. Layer bread, then drained sausage. Add cheese over the sausage. Beat eggs well with milk, pepper, salt and the mustard. Pour over the sausage and cheese mixture. Let set overnight in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Sprinkle with coconut and put under broiler until toasted.

title: ma ma's chili sauce
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions finely.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Stir well.
Add spices tied in cheesecloth.
Bring to boil, then simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Stir often.
Should cook down to 1/2 starting amount.
Pack in sterilized jars.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix the mixed fruit, peaches and pear halves, reserving liquid. Add pineapple chunks and juice.
Add entire can of concentrated frozen orange juice and some of the reserved liquid, if needed, to cover all the fruit.
Save remaining reserved liquid to add after adding bananas and kiwi, if needed, to cover fruit.
Chill.
Before serving, add sliced bananas and kiwi.
This is a good salad to take out or serve if having friends in for breakfast.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix with water, stirring with a fork until blended.
Press mixture in bottom of a lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Cook ground beef, pepper and onion in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Spoon mixture over crust.
Combine sour cream, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spoon over meat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into squares.

title: angel icing
directions: Beat all ingredients together until thick.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (6 cups).
Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery and onions.
Chop egg whites.
Add sieved yolks, mixed with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Fold into salad.
Add salt and celery seed.
Chill 2 hours.

title: banana-nut cake royale
directions: Cream 3/4 cup shortening with 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bananas; beat for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with buttermilk to banana mixture.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat for 2 minutes longer.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into 2 greased layer cake pans; sprinkle half the coconut over each layer.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pans; cool, coconut side up, on wire racks.

title: tony's coca-cola barbecue sauce
directions: Precook about 2 pounds of pork or chicken.
Mix ingredients and brush onto meat.
Add more Coke if needed.
Barbecue until meat develops a nice glaze.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces in a large Pyrex dish. Mix strawberry glaze and sliced fresh strawberries together; place on top of cake.
Mix together the 4x sugar, sour cream and Cool Whip together.
Put on top.
This is best when you make it into 2 layers.

title: parsleyed new potatoes
directions: Cook new potatoes in jackets.
Remove jackets. Combine butter, lemon juice and parsley. Add potatoes; toss until coated. Serves 6.

title: lemon cheese squares
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve one cup and pat the rest lightly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and the other egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: snicker salad
directions: Mix it up and love it!

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown chicken and drain.
Put in a baking dish.
Saute onion and butter.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour; baste.

title: whole grain jam squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except the preserves, in large mixing bowl; beat at low speed with electric mixer until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups mixture, press remaining into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread preserves evenly over this base; sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Beat egg whites; add sugar and salt.
Add nuts and stir until covered with mixture.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts over butter and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: nina ice cream
directions: Dry Ingredients (7 cups total).
Use 2 to 3 cups of oatmeal as base.

Add remainder to make 7 cups, using any combinations of wheat germ, cornmeal, powdered milk, whole wheat flour, Grape-Nuts, coconut, wheat bran, grits, sunflower seeds, sesame seed, uncooked cereal (like Ralston), nuts and spices.
Create your own combinations according to your likes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Heat in pan.
Serve with slice of lemon and "spot" of butter.

title: iris' brown sugar maple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, and oil until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until mixed.
Add flour and salt, alternating with the milk; beat until smooth.
Add nuts coated with flour and flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: reduced sodium swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from steak and coat with flour and pepper.
Pound meat with edge of plate or wooden mallet to tenderize before meat is floured if desired.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown steak on both sides; remove steak from skillet.
Saute onion in skillet.
Add tomatoes, beef broth, vegetable juice and meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrot pieces and simmer until carrots are tender. Makes 6 servings, 226 calories; 252 mg. sodium per serving.

title: mexican stuffed potato
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave until soft, cut in half lengthwise. Remove pulp and mash with sour cream and milk. Combine with beans, corn, cilantro, salt and pepper. Mound mixture into potato skins. Top with cheese. Bake 20 minutes in 400 degree oven. Serve with salsa.

title: no-bake honey balls
directions: Crush the Corn Flakes to a fine consistency.
Mix together the peanut butter and honey.
Gradually add nonfat dry milk.
Grease hands.
Form mixture into balls and roll in crushed flakes.
Let balls set on wax paper, then serve.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potato, sugar and vanilla together.
Roll out like a pie shell.
Cover with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Add nuts on top of peanut butter, then roll up into a roll and slice into about 1/2 to 1-inch slices.

title: chicken pastries
directions: Preheat oven to
Blend cream cheese and melted butter. Mix well and add chicken and rest of ingredients.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles, pressing dotted separation lines together. Place 1/4 chicken mixture on each rectangle. Bring corners together and twist.
Press sides together. Brush tops with melted butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan and bake 20 minutes.

title: pork chops with apple-corn bread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Season pork with 1/2 teaspoon thyme, then salt and pepper.
Melt 1/2 tablespoon butter in heavy medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork chops to skillet; saute until cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.
Transfer pork chops to small baking pan.

title: strawberry supreme salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain.
Let set 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage. Melt fat in pan and put in cabbage.
Warm cabbage, season with salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cook in.
Cover and cook for approximately 15 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and Italian dressing mix together with fork.
Spread cheese mixture on bread, top with cucumber slice.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce.
Mix flour, soda, spices and salt together and sift into other mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Bring 3 cups water and sugar to a boil for three minutes and cool completely.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Pour water/sugar combination over fruit and freeze overnight.
Let thaw 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Refreeze balance.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces; bread and fry.
Cut chunky pineapple pieces in half.
Cut up peppers.
Add pineapple, peppers and 2 cups of water to chicken.
Simmer until peppers are done. Thicken with cornstarch (2 to 3 tablespoons).
Serve over rice.

title: danish red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan. Simmer until tender. Serve with roast pork or turkey. Serves 8.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine according to package and drain.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, saute onion, garlic in melted butter or margarine. Add clams with juice, salt, basil and pepper.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve clam sauce over hot linguine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: quick and easy beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, macaroni and Miracle Whip; heat.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Heat in stove at 325° until cheese melts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook and drain noodles, then rinse with cold water.
Layer into crock-pot, hamburger, noodles, sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Keep layering until you end with cheese on top.
Cook on low for 5 hours.

title: jell-o salad
directions: Mix pudding, Jell-O and water and bring to a boil.
Let cool and add Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: sesame london broil
directions: Heat oil and toast seed lightly.
Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Turn once or twice.
Cook in oven at 350° until desired wellness.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium-high heat for 2 minutes (bacon will not be done).
Flatten chicken slightly with palm of hand.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Place chicken breasts in bacon drippings in skillet.
Cook 6 minutes on each side or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Add tomatoes, olives and garlic to skillet.
Cook uncovered about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash cream cheese in bowl by hand.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well and mash by hand again.
Serve with crackers.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Bake in two unbaked pie shells for 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: peachy chicken
directions: You will need 4 pieces heavy-duty aluminum foil (you can use 2 pieces of regular weight foil).

title: deer meat marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients into a medium size bowl.
Marinate about 1 to 2 hours.
Then discard the solution.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayo and seasonings.
Stir in chopped onions, spinach, chopped water chestnuts and red peppers.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crisp or assorted crackers.
Makes 3 1/2 cups dip.

title: candy mints
directions: Work with hands until soft and smooth, of dough like consistency, and color is uniform. Press into candy molds, level with knife; carefully turn out onto waxed paper.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Mix together and heat in crock-pot for at least one hour before serving.
May cook longer to increase flavor.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix bread, butter, shrimp, salt, pepper, cheese.
Mix eggs and milk.
Combine these two mixtures and pour into greased casserole dish.
Set dish in pan of hot water in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Crush in a plastic bag the 2 stacks of Ritz crackers.
Mix with all of the ingredients in a casserole dish.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with any kind of crackers or raw vegetables.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Make pastry according to package directions, rolling to 2-12 inch rounds. Refrigerate. Preheat oven to 450°. In a large bowl, combine rhubarb, sugar, flour, eggs, lemon juice and salt. Put into pastry lined pie plate. Dot with butter. Place remaining pastry on top of rhubarb mixture, cutting slits in pie crust for steam vents. Moisten edge of pastry with a little water. Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. sugar. Bake for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Butter a 12 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Place drained peas in bottom, next add drained asparagus, water chestnuts, sliced drained mushrooms, sliced eggs, salt and pepper.
Spread soup over top. Place slices of cheese over all and sprinkle top with onion rings. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fat-free corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Mix wet ingredients. Blend together. Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8-inch square pan or 15 to 20 minutes in muffin pans.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice to a boil.
Add gelatin and mix well, then cool.
Add buttermilk, nondairy whipped topping and nuts.
Mix well and congeal.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain
cooked spinach and mix all ingredients together. Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and margarine.
Pat down in greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle nuts.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, eggs, then rest of ingredients. Pour in greased pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best green salad i ever et
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mint leaves and lettuce, in large, flat-bottomed salad bowl, and refrigerate for 30 minutes to 1 hour. When ready to serve, add lettuce and mint leaves; toss.

title: burger mushroom bake
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients except water. Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water; pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stirring constantly, bring water, pudding and jello to a full boil. Remove from heat and allow to cool while preparing strawberries. Slice strawberries and arrange evenly in pie crust. Spread glaze over strawberries and chill until firm. Cool Whip Lite optional.

title: hamburger oriental
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix well all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Then 45 minutes uncovered. Freezes great!

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook rice until golden brown in skillet in cooking oil.
Add tomato sauce, water, lemon juice, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until rice is done.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Place bread in 9x13 buttered dish.
Mix sausage and cheese and spread over bread.
Add milk and mustard to beaten eggs and pour over bread, sausage and cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees for about 1 hour. Makes about 12 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in salted water for a few minutes to soften.
Drain.
Mix 2 tablespoons soup with the rest of the ingredients.
Divide mixture among cabbage leaves, fold in sides and roll up, securing with toothpick.
Place rolls seam side down in pot and pour soup over them.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes. Stir now and then spooning sauce over rolls.

title: apples and cheese
directions: Mix flour
and
sugar.
Cut in the butter.
Stir in the cheese.
Pour
the apples into a lightly greased pie plate and sprinkle the dry
mixture
over
the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good served with pork.

title: smoke sosich
directions: in pot boil sosich for 30 minits.

title: potatoes laritan
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 c. butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a large bowl, mix soup and sour cream.
Stir well but do not over-stir, as the cream will break down.
Stir in the onion mixture and add the potatoes.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Melt the remaining 1/4 c. butter and mix with the crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
It bubbles up, so make sure the pan is deep enough.

title: italian style beef and bean soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, onions and garlic until juices evaporate and beef is well browned, stirring frequently.
With slotted spoon, remove beef mixture to bowl.

To drippings remaining in Dutch oven, add cabbage and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until cabbage is tender, adding 1 tablespoon salad oil, if necessary. Return beef mixture to Dutch oven, add tomatoes with their liquid and next 4 ingredients (water, salt, bouillon and oregano).
Heat to boiling over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in beans and 1/2 cup grated cheese; heat through.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix well. Layer in a dish: wafers, bananas and pudding.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: turmeric slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, celery, peppers and onions in large bowl.
Bring remaining ingredients to a hard boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Refrigerate.
Will keep a couple of months.
In fact, the longer you keep it, the crisper it gets.

title: pull candy
directions: Add the sugar, light brown sugar and water. Important: do not stir mixture. Bring to 240°, then add the margarine. Do not stir. Bring to 265°. Add the vanilla. Pour on buttered marble slab; should be cold marble. Let cool enough to start pulling. Take outside and pull. When it has been pulled enough, cut with buttered scissors. Necessary to be cold weather and not raining or snowing.

title: tuna and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add mayonnaise and onion.
Add grated cheese, soup, tuna and peas.
Mix by hand.
Top with crumbled crackers and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lynda sudduth's cheese puffs
directions: Mix dough combining butter and cheese.
Add salt and paprika to flour; mix and add to cheese and butter mixture.
Use dough to make balls around olives and onions.
Freeze until needed.
When ready to fix, put in oven on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 400°. Serve hot.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into bite-size pieces and brown in large skillet.
In separate skillet cook onion in butter until limp. Combine both skillets and add mushroom soup, sour cream, water and paprika.
Simmer about 1 hour until meat is tender.
Serve on hot buttered noodles.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to break into small pieces.
Then drain off grease.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Spoon into a 3-quart casserole or in 2 small casseroles. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make small meat balls.
Cook in skillet and drain off fat.
Mix 12-ounce bottle chili sauce, and 10-ounce grape jelly.
Heat.
Put in meat balls and simmer.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pastry crust
directions: Place flour in bowl; cut lard into flour, using a pastry blender until mixture is the size of small peas.
Place egg, lemon juice, baking powder and salt in a glass measuring cup.
Add enough water to equal 1/2 cup.
Pour liquid into flour mixture and toss lightly just to moisten.
Divide dough in half and form into 2 balls; freeze 1 ball for future use and refrigerate 1 ball for 1/2 hour.
Roll out dough to fit a 9-inch pie pan; trim.
Roll out remaining dough.
Cut for top crust.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden, at 400°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Use leftover mashed potatoes from refrigerator.
For every two cups potatoes, add 4 tablespoons flour, 1/2 cup onion and 1 egg. Stir ingredients and make into patties.
Fry in skillet until brown on each side.

title: country fried steak and gravy
directions: Drop meat pieces into whole milk and let stand for 15 minutes. Remove from milk and dip into flour, coating each piece well. Sprinkle with pepper.
Drop into deep hot oil and fry quickly until brown on both sides.

title: strawberry-cherry butter
directions: Blend all the ingredients well.
Try on hot biscuits.
Yields 2/3 cup.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl the Seven-Up and Hawaiian Punch.
Carefully put in sherbet.
Great for parties.

title: diet snickers
directions: Mix all together and spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze and cut into 8 bars.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Blend potted meat and cream cheese.
Spread evenly on ham slices.
Roll slices.
Place in freezer.
When frozen, remove and cut into pinwheels.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: chicken sansford
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Coat inside chicken first, with mayonnaise mixture, then sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs. After you have done each piece, place chicken in greased Pyrex dish.
Make a foil tent over them.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
During last 20 minutes, remove tent and place about 3/4 cup hot water in pan for added juice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, 1 cup powdered sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Mix well and line pan.
Mix powdered sugar, egg whites and butter; mix 10 minutes and pour over crust.
Spread pineapple over that.
Spread bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans over Cool Whip.
Place cherries on top.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: jiffy barbeque sauce
directions: Cook onion until soft in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Delicious on everything!

title: german rice
directions: Cook rice and other ingredients in broth.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cook 35 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Margarine should be at room temperature.
Cream first four ingredients together until light and fluffy in large mixing bowl. Sift together next four ingredients and add gradually to creamed mixture.
Place mixture in refrigerator to chill for a minimum of 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add milk.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into the batter.
Mix well and add 1/2 cup nuts (optional).

title: creamy tacos
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for Velveeta and Fritos. Simmer.
After burner has been turned off, add Velveeta.
Serve over Fritos.

title: lorri's sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and drain.
Mash potatoes and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry salad(can be frozen)
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries (thawed and mashed) and blend.
Add crushed pineapple (drained and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat egg, milk and margarine.
Add egg mixture and sour cream to flour mixture.
Stir until blended. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add rest of the ingredients in order.
Bake in 3 loaf pans for about 30 minutes or tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 325°.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Drain pineapple and blot with paper towel.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, then chill until you can shape into ball.
Roll into ball; add pecans onto top.

title: wok broccoli
directions: Cut up broccoli, scallions and mushrooms into small pieces. Put a drop of oil in bottom of wok.
Heat.
Add broccoli pieces. Cover and mix.
Cook 1 minute.
Add water.
Cover for one minute. Add mushrooms, scallions, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Mix.
Cover and cook 1 more minute.

title: date nut balls
directions: Chop the dates and heat with sugar and margarine until margarine is melted.
Remove from the heat and add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
When cool enough to handle, shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, vanilla, and powdered sugar together.
(May need to mix with hands to mix really well.)
Roll into 1-inch round balls and place on a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper or foil.
Place cookie sheet with buckeyes into freezer to chill.

title: peppermint brownie meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, 1/3 cup of butter and peppermint extract.
Stir in milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, until spreading consistency.
Spread over brownies.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until frosting is firm. Heat chocolate and 2 teaspoons butter until melted.
