Drizzle evenly over frosting; spread evenly.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes or until chocolate is firm.
Cut into 1 1/2 or 2-inch squares. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 or 24 brownies.

title: white nut loaf
directions: Mix together thoroughly sugar and shortening, then egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture, beating as little as possible.
Add nuts and stir only until nuts are blended into mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 1/5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan and spread from center to ends and outer edges. Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes. An excellent tea bread, not too sweet.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in saucepan. Pour over cereal and mix until coated.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Melt
butter in an oblong baking dish; add single layer of potatoes.
Turn
potatoes
once
in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients;
sprinkle over the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until the top of the potatoes are crisp and brown.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Then add the soy sauce and the seeds.
Stir until brown.
Add salt as desired.
Cool before serving.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water and boil for 6 minutes. Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Cool.
Either combine dry strawberries with cooled gelatin and pour into pie shell or place berries in pie shell and pour cooled mixture over them. Refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cajun crabs and rice
directions: Cook rice in 3 cups water until just tender.
While rice is cooking, saute onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes with juice, Cajun seasoning, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaves and cloves.
Bring mixture to a simmer, then reduce heat to low.
Add crab meat.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix and flour the raisins, fruit and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sausage and water.
Sift flour, soda and spices together; add to sausage.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Fold in other ingredients.
Bake in well greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour or longer.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook pie crust and let cool.
Sift together sugar and cornstarch.
Take egg yolks and 1/4 cup milk and beat well, add rest of milk.
Add sugar to milk mixture and cook stirring constantly until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla, stir well and place in refrigerator until cool.
Place in pie shell and top with beaten egg whites (12 tablespoons sugar to egg whites) or Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.

title: veggie salad
directions: Mix all of ingredients. Let marinate.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, pineapple juice, beaten egg yolks, cornstarch and butter in top of double boiler and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and cool.
After it has cooled, pour in drained fruit cocktail, chopped apples, bananas, nuts and pineapple.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion soup mix. Combine cream of chicken soup and milk and pour over chicken. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cover with foil for the first part of baking time.
This is a great recipe for Sunday dinner after church.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add to heated milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly, and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into crackers and cooked mixture with vanilla.
Chill until serving.
You may add a topping.

title: baked figs
directions: Wash figs and remove stems, but do not peel. Place in shallow dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice and brown sugar to taste. Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: green grape pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, cinnamon, water and grapes together.
Stir over low heat until thick, about 5 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Chill.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter.
Set aside 3/4 cup of this mixture.
Add baking powder, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread 2 cups blueberries over batter.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fish stick surprise
directions: Place thawed fish in single layer in shallow pan.
Combine dressing, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over fish and let stand 30 minutes, turning once.
Remove fish from sauce and place single layer in well-greased baking pan.
Combine onion and cheese. Sprinkle over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easy.

title: frosted chocolate cone cakes
directions: Make 1 box chocolate cake mix and follow directions on it. Pour into ice cream cones until 1-inch from top.
Put the ice cream cones in a muffin tin and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Bake right away so cones don't get soggy.
When cooled, frost with your favorite frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water; add jello and dissolve.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix well, then add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and process in food processor.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Goes good with bread chunks, crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: easy cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla flavoring. Add nondairy whipped topping. Place in pie crust. Top with blueberries. Keep refrigerated.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Dip slices of bread into mixture and place on a hot frying pan.
Turn bread over when the side that is down turns brown.
Remove from pan when other side gets brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken wings in pan and heat to boiling, simmering for 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken wings. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Baste occasionally.

title: jello pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O and let set (not too solid) and whip.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, rind and juice of lemon.
Whip evaporated milk and mix with Jell-O mixture.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon, 1/4 cup sugar and shortening.
Cover pan.
Sprinkle a few nuts on top and a little of graham cracker mixture.
Form graham cracker mix in 8-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter ice cream #1
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter and milk in blender or mixer; mix until smooth.
Pour into 1-gallon ice cream freezer.
Add enough homogenized milk to reach fill line.
Freeze with ice and ice cream salt.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: rock cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix soda and hot water.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add beaten eggs, chopped nuts and dates.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add to mixture.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet on medium-high heat. Stir in barbecue sauce, water, corn and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan candies
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Dip pecans in butter.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave in 30 more minutes.

title: bittersweet brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Beat in eggs, corn syrup and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts. Spread in prepared pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until soft in center and edges are slightly firm.
Do not overbake.
Let cool completely before frosting and cutting into squares.

title: salsa fresca(fresh salsa)
directions: Finely chop all vegetables.
Squeeze juice of lime in a bowl and mix in Tabasco sauce, vinegar and salt. Stir and incorporate the vegetables.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Serve cool with your favorite chips.

title: cheesy chili corn quidre
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan or 10-inch quiche dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned around edge.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Fold in ice cream.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and sausage.	Melt Velveeta cheese over meat sauce.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Place small amount on slices of rye bread.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.	If you like a spicy taste, you can use hot sausage and/or Mexican-style Velveeta cheese.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown bacon; set aside.
Add flour to drippings and brown to make roux.
Add 1 quart water or broth to roux.
Saute onions, pepper and celery in margarine; add to roux mixture.
Add sausage and tomatoes. Add okra and cook.
Add shrimp and chicken last, cook until done.
Add gumbo file to taste.
Makes a large pot.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Just as it begins to thicken, fold in 2/3 of the Cool Whip.
Add cake pieces and fold together until well coated.
Pour into an angel food pan (tube pan) and put in refrigerator to set.
Unmold onto cake plate and ice with remaining Cool Whip tinted a pale pink.

title: pasta chicken salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Mix together salad dressings and pour over pasta mix.
Toss, refrigerate for 4 hours to blend flavors.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients,
then add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pork and zucchini
directions: Brown pork chops or pork steaks; dice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cumin and garlic powder.
Dice zucchini and add to pork.
Add whole corn and tomatoes.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until squash is tender.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook orzo according to package directions; drain.
In 5 quart saucepan, brown bacon; drain.
Add onion and parsley; cook until onion is tender but not brown.
Stir in 3 1/2 cup milk, orzo, butter, salt and pepper.
Add corn and bacon; simmer for 20 minutes.
While cooking, blend together flour and remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Stir into corn mixture; cook and stir until bubbly. Stir about 1 cup of hot mixture into the egg and return the mix to the chowder.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes more.
Garnish with chives.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned lye soap
directions: Bring lye and water to a boil in iron kettle.
Add cracklings and boil 2 hours.
When the mixture looks like syrup and all cracklings heat up, add Borax and ammonia.
If you add oil of sassafras, it will have a nice scent.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter.
Let cool.
Mix together all ingredients (but chocolate and wax).
Roll into balls.
Let sit overnight in fridge.
Melt chocolate (over water) and add the wax.
Dip with a fork.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sweetener, flour, spices and salt; mix with apples. Line pie plate with pastry; fill with apple mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Place top crust on pie; sprinkle with sugar substitute, if desired. Bake at 400° for about 50 minutes or until done. Yield: 8 servings.
Carbohydrate 9 g, protein 3 g, fat 1.6 g, calories 220.
One serving = 2 bread exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.
Add extra nutritional values depending on pie crust you use.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Mix with all the ingredients, except cheese.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add remaining mixture on top of cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; blend thoroughly.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with half the pie dough, rolled 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle about 1/4 the sugar mixture over the bottom.
Arrange sliced apples and remaining sugar mixture in the pan and lemon juice over the top. Dot with butter.
Adjust the top crust, cutting several vents to allow for the escape of steam.
Trim and seal edges.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Then reduce the heat to 350° and continue to bake for 45 minutes longer or until the apples are tender.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Combine macaroni and cheese mixture; mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with breadcrumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.

title: strawberry muffins(yield: 12 muffins)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 450°.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Note:
Cheddar cheese may be put on top, if desired.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups and tomatoes with enough broth to be soupy, not watery.
Line bottom of 2-quart casserole dish with Doritos. Pour layer of mixture over Doritos.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and add more Doritos. Add more mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and cover with grated cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Five minutes before cake is done, bring oleo and milk to boil. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over hot cake.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together. Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to the egg mixture with some of the flour being the last addition. Add lemon extract. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dessert cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together using the instant pudding dry as it comes form the package.
Roll into a ball and chill over night. Serve with cinnamon graham crackers or ginger snaps

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Put Karo syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill.

title: dates with bacon
directions: Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Wrap piece of bacon around date. Secure with a toothpick (can be frozen at this point).
Lay on baking sheet and put into oven heated to 375 degrees.
Cook until bacon is done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Spread rice in bottom of pan and pour soup over chicken; sprinkle onion soup mix over this.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: grape jello
directions: Mix together. Boil 20 minutes.

title: church windows
directions: You will also need waxed paper.

title: canned sweet peppers
directions: Combine green, red and yellow pepper quarters with water to cover in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cook for 4 minutes; drain.
Pack in 4 hot, sterilized quart jars.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and 1 teaspoon salt to each jar.
Combine 1 quart water, vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Pour over peppers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Yield:
64 servings.

title: orange-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix in order as listed, then congeal.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; spread bread slices with margarine. Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and salt and mix well. Pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.

title: chili by ellis
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pot until hot.
Do not boil.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Crumble Ritz crackers.
Mix with melted oleo.
Add to vegetables last 10 minutes of baking.

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop by heaping tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes.
Melt butter and combine with the garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing them from the cookie sheet. Makes 10-12 biscuits.

title: world's best spinach dip(chill time: 2 hours. prep: 10 min. chill: 2 hrs)
directions: In medium bowl, combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, recipe mix, and green onions.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water and add 1 1/2 cups cold water (no pineapple juice).
Beat cranberry sauce lightly. Add sauce, pineapple, orange and nuts when jello begins to set.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix the flour, chopped nuts and oleo.
Pat into a glass baking pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: vegetable and meatball soup
directions: Combine ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and bring mixture to a boil.

title: corn and muffin bake
directions: Combine muffin mix with sour cream, eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° until browned lightly.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Melt butter; then add flour, salt, red pepper, parsley and nutmeg.
Cook for 1 minute and then add milk.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add crab meat. May be held at this point.
When ready to serve, stir in heated cream and sherry.
Serves 4.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, lemon peel and parsley.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles.
Blend in sour cream.
Add beans; heat through, stirring.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese.
Combine margarine and bread crumbs; sprinkle over beans.
Broil just until cheese melts and crumbs brown.

title: greek corn bread
directions: Place in lightly
buttered
or
oiled square baking pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: layered tostada bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease oblong baking dish, 12 x 7 x 2-inches.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, beans, chilies and olives.
Mix 1 egg, baking mix, cornmeal, milk and oil until moistened.
Beat 30 seconds.

title: creamy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen until tender, adding salt and pepper to taste. Cook and debone. Boil spaghetti in broth.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert or salad
directions: In another
bowl
whip	1
cup	double cream.
Then mix jello mixture with other bowl of ingredients; then fold in the whipped cream.

title: banana dressing
directions: Peel and slice the banana and put into food processor fitted with the steel blade.
Add powdered sugar, lemon juice and the Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Remove to a serving bowl; fold in whipping cream.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix flour, bran, spices and soda together in a bowl.
Put the milk and orange juice in another bowl and lightly beat in the eggs.
Put margarine, sugar and molasses in a saucepan on low heat and stir until sugar has dissolved.
Remove from heat, stir in the dry ingredients and then add the egg mixture.
Pour into a 2 lb. loaf pan lined with baking parchment and bake for 40 minutes.

title: cornbread stuffing for roast turkey
directions: Prepare cornbread mix and bake as package label directs.
Let cornbread cool, then crumble into large bowl.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute celery and onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add parsley, sage, thyme, salt and pepper.
With fork, stir eggs, broth and vegetable mixture into crumbled cornbread.
Toss lightly until well combined.
To stuff and truss turkey, spoon stuffing into neck cavity.
Bring skin of neck over back; fasten with poultry pins.
Then spoon dressing lightly into body cavity of bird; do not pack.

Insert about 5 poultry pins at regular intervals to draw body opening together. With twine, lace cavity closed, bootlace fashion; tie with knot. Bend wing tips under body or fasten to body with poultry pins. With twine, tie ends of legs together.
Makes about 12 cups (enough to fill a 10 to 12 pound ready to cook turkey).

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a heavy 3-quart pan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Melt margarine; add Bisquick and sour cream.
Mix well.
Drop into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: three bean casserole *
directions: Drain and chop water chestnuts.
Add next six ingredients. Chill this topping overnight.

title: chicken ro-tel
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from broth.
Cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Boil noodles in chicken broth.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into a large baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ukrainian meat loaf
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters and remove cores.
Cover with boiling water and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
In bowl, mix ground beef, beef broth, parsley and onion.
Put 2 strips of bacon on bottom of loaf pan.
Cover with layer of cabbage, then layer of meat mix.
Alternate cabbage and meat layers, ending with meat. Cover with 3 strips of bacon.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat loaf.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and place on cake rack.
Allow to set about 15 minutes or remove from oven and turn out of pan onto foil.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa, Coke and marshmallows until it boils.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture. Mix well and add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Beat well. Pour in greased and floured pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: a pot of dried beans or black-eyed peas
directions: Pick over beans or peas to remove any bad ones; wash them. Put them and the meat in a big pot and cover with water.
Slow boil for about 2 hours or until done.
Put the salt in during the last hour.
Serve with cornbread or biscuits.

title: easy chicken and rice wraps
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, melt margarine. Saute rice-vermicelli mix until vermicelli is golden brown. Add 2 cups water, salsa, chicken and special seasonings. Bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat to low. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and chicken is cooked through. Stir in beans and corn; let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serve in tortillas with cheese and sour cream. Serves 4.

title: buttermilk sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk, in three separate portions.
"Drop dough from tablespoon in order to make large cookies.
Small cookies will not have the center texture desired in this cookie."
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar or just sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Watch closely, they should not brown.
Finished cookie should be 4-inches across to have a soft center.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the first four ingredients.
Sprinkle dry salad dressing over the top of the first four ingredients. Seal the salad with as much mayonnaise as necessary.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese to taste over top of mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: date pudding
directions: To 3 cups boiling water, add brown sugar and butter.
Boil 3 minutes.
Put in 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients together, adding dates and nuts last.
Drop dough mixture by teaspoon on top of water-sugar mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic.
Mix well. Add cheese, broccoli and noodles.
Mix lightly.
Chill. Arrange tomatoes on serving platter.
Top with vegetable mixture. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef and rice for two
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, saute rice in oil until golden brown.
Add the water, bouillon, celery, green pepper, onion and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in the beef.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: fresh peach bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add peaches.
Mix flour, cinnamon,
baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in two pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: tiny puffs
directions: Melt margarine in water and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Let cool.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes or until brown. Cool and split center and fill with chicken salad or any party filling.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Pare eggplant and slice into 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Dip first in eggs, then in crumbs.
Saute in hot oil until brown on both sides.
In 2-quart casserole, place layer of eggplant.
Cover with Parmesan cheese, oregano and sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Cover well with tomato sauce.
Repeat until all eggplant has been used. Top last with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: party spinach cups
directions: Lightly grease 20 miniature muffin cups.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add spinach, mushrooms, bread crumbs, cheese, yogurt, salt and pepper; blend well.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits, then separate each into 2 layers.
Place each layer in greased muffin cup and press firmly in bottom and up sides.
Spoon generous tablespoon spinach mixture into each cup.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Garnish each with sour cream, if desired.
Serve warm. Makes 20 appetizers.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, then oil, mixing well.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with back of spoon.
Bake 24 minutes or until light brown in a 325° oven.
Allow to cool on sheets before removing onto cooling racks.

title: goulash
directions: While cooking shells in big pot, brown hamburger and drain. Chop tomatoes.
Drain shells. Mix shells, hamburger and tomatoes. Serves 6.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and margarine.
Beat in the egg, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Add slowly the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in shapes and put on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Don't let them get too brown on bottom.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and salad oil; add sugar, stir until dissolved. Cool.
Pour over kraut and rest of ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator 24 hours.
Very good with meat and poultry.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in frypan and add rest of ingredients, stirring as you go along.
Simmer for 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup and butter.
Mix well.
Line pie shell with pecans.
Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: In pot, combine potatoes with enough water to cover by 1-inch over high heat; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; cook until tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain, return to pot.
Mash until smooth; cool 15 minutes.

title: pizzelles
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by tablespoonful onto pizzelle iron.

title: crispy cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all in order given.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butternut squash puree
directions: Melt butter in heavy sauce pan; saute onion until soft.
Add squash, turnip and pears and simmer, covered, until soft (about 15 minutes).
Add water if needed.
Puree in food processor until smooth.
Season to taste.

title: texas beef stew
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, brown beef, adding oil.
If desired, drain.
Add onion, garlic powder, pepper and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add tomatoes and cumin.
Reduce heat and cook until done.
Makes 1 quart, 4 servings.

title: mom's best cranberry salad
directions: Prepare the raspberry gelatin according to package directions. Garnish with whole pecans on top.
Refrigerate to set.
Mix the first 7 ingredients together; pour over jelled gelatin.

title: dill dip for veggies
directions: Mix and refrigerate for a few hours before serving!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes. When done, mash and cream potatoes until very fluffy. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Add marshmallows the last 10
minutes of cooking.

title: marinated whole green beans
directions: Drain liquid off beans and marinate in the above mixture overnight.
Serve cold.

title: tamale dip
directions: Chop up tamales; cut up cheese in large hunks.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serve hot with chips.

title: creamy lebanese tuna salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix yogurt, scallions, dill, salt and pepper.
Add cucumber and tuna and toss gently.
Just before serving, line pitas with spinach and fill each with half of the tuna mixture. Makes 2 servings.

title: taco casserole ii
directions: Brown meat; add taco seasoning and cook according to package directions.
Crush Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer remaining ingredients in the following order:
Layer meat on top of Doritos, then onion, tomato, lettuce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
(Chop ingredients ahead of time.
Put together just prior to baking to prevent Doritos/Tostitos from getting soggy.)

title: butterscotch-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, butter, Crisco (butter flavor), vanilla and oil until creamy; add eggs and beat for 2 minutes.
Add sifted flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt slowly.
Mix in with chocolate chip and butterscotch chips, also nutmeats.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Blend ground beef, rice, pepper, celery salt and onion.
Form into 24 balls.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soup, tomato sauce and water; pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in skillet.
Cook until spins a thread.
Add peanuts; cook until brown or color changes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour into buttered dish.
Then break into pieces.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease quart casserole.
Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Put layer of potatoes, onion and cheese. Pour soup mixture over top.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Remove, cover and bake until done, about 15 minutes longer.

title: butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil in Dutch oven, do not add salt.
Saute mushrooms in butter after meat.
Grease casserole.
Mix well all ingredients with meat.
Cover and bake 2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: nut tarts
directions: Mix crust ingredients; form into 24 balls.
Line 24 small muffin tins by pressing dough around in each muffin tin.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and pudding mix; fold in.
Do not beat.
Chill and serve.
